  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Wickedness of Judah'
      title: The Wickedness of Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  The vision of Isaiah the son of Amoz, which he saw concerning Judah
        and Jerusalem in the days of Uzziah, Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah, kings of
        Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "  Hear, O heavens, and give ear, O earth;for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has spoken:\u201CChildren[[COMMENT(0)]]  have I reared and brought up,but
        they have rebelled against me.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:2 '
        content: Or ; also verse 4
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The ox knows its owner,and the donkey its master\u2019s crib,but
        Israel does not know,my people do not understand.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Ah, sinful nation,a people laden with iniquity,  offspring of evildoers,children
        who deal corruptly!They have forsaken the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,they
        have despised the Holy One of Israel,they are utterly estranged.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Why will you still be struck down?Why will you continue to rebel?The
        whole head is sick,and the whole heart faint.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  From the sole of the foot even to the head,there is no soundness
        in it,but bruises and soresand raw wounds;they are not pressed out or bound
        upor softened with oil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  Your country lies desolate;your cities are burned with fire;in
        your very presenceforeigners devour your land;it is desolate, as overthrown
        by foreigners.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the daughter of Zion is leftlike a booth in a vineyard,like a
        lodge in a cucumber field,like a besieged city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  If the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hostshad not left us a few
        survivors,we should have been like Sodom,and become like Gomorrah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Hear the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,you rulers of Sodom!Give
        ear to the teaching[[COMMENT(0)]] of our God,you people of Gomorrah!  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:10 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "  \u201CWhat to me is the multitude of your sacrifices?says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;I
        have had enough of burnt offerings of ramsand the fat of well-fed beasts;I
        do not delight in the blood of bulls,or of lambs, or of goats.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CWhen you come to appear before me,who has required of youthis
        trampling of my courts?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Bring no more vain offerings;incense is an abomination to me.  New
        moon and Sabbath and the calling of convocations\u2014I cannot endure iniquity
        and solemn assembly.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Your new moons and your appointed feastsmy soul hates;they have become
        a burden to me;I am weary of bearing them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When you spread out your hands,I will hide my eyes from you;  even
        though you make many prayers,I will not listen;  your hands are full of blood.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  Wash yourselves; make yourselves clean;remove the evil of your
        deeds from before my eyes;  cease to do evil,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "learn to do good;  seek justice,correct oppression;  bring justice
        to the fatherless,plead the widow\u2019s cause.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CCome now, let us reason[[COMMENT(0)]] together, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:though
        your sins are like scarlet,they shall be as white as snow;though they are
        red like crimson,they shall become like wool.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:18 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  If you are willing and obedient,you shall eat the good of the land;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: The Unfaithful City'
      title: The Unfaithful City
      number: 20
      content: "but if you refuse and rebel,you shall be eaten by the sword;  for
        the mouth of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has spoken.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'How the faithful city  has become a whore,[[COMMENT(0)]]  she who
        was full of justice!Righteousness lodged in her,but now murderers.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:21 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  Your silver has become dross,your best wine mixed with water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Your princes are rebelsand companions of thieves.Everyone loves a
        bribeand runs after gifts.  They do not bring justice to the fatherless,and
        the widow\u2019s cause does not come to them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Therefore the Lord declares,the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts,the
        Mighty One of Israel:\u201CAh, I will get relief from my enemies  and avenge
        myself on my foes.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  I will turn my hand against youand will smelt away your dross as
        with lyeand remove all your alloy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And I will restore your judges as at the first,and your counselors
        as at the beginning.Afterward you shall be called the city of righteousness,the
        faithful city.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '  Zion shall be redeemed by justice,and those in her who repent,
        by righteousness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '  But rebels and sinners shall be broken together,and those who forsake
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> shall be consumed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '  For they[[COMMENT(0)]] shall be ashamed of the oaksthat you desired;and
        you shall blush for the gardensthat you have chosen.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:29 '
        content: 'Some Hebrew manuscripts '
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'For you shall be like an oakwhose leaf withers,and like a garden
        without water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: And the strong shall become tinder,and his work a spark,and both of
        them shall burn together,with none to quench them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Mountain of the '
      title: 'The Mountain of the '
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  The word that Isaiah the son of Amoz
        saw concerning Judah and Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  It shall come to pass in the latter daysthat the mountain of the
        house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>shall be established as the highest
        of the mountains,and shall be lifted up above the hills;and all the nations
        shall flow to it,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and many peoples shall come, and say:\u201CCome, let us go up to
        the mountain of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,to the house of the God of
        Jacob,that he may teach us his waysand that we may walk in his paths.\u201DFor
        out of Zion shall go forth the law,[[COMMENT(0)]]and the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        from Jerusalem.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:3 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He shall judge between the nations,and shall decide disputes for
        many peoples;  and they shall beat their swords into plowshares,and their
        spears into pruning hooks;  nation shall not lift up sword against nation,neither
        shall they learn war anymore.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: The Day of the '
      title: 'The Day of the '
      number: 5
      content: 'O house of Jacob,come, let us walkin the light of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For you have rejected your people,the house of Jacob,because they
        are full of things from the eastand of fortune-tellers like the Philistines,and
        they strike hands with the children of foreigners.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Their land is filled with silver and gold,and there is no end to
        their treasures;their land is filled with horses,and there is no end to their
        chariots.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Their land is filled with idols;they bow down to the work of their
        hands,to what their own fingers have made.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So man is humbled,and each one is brought low\u2014do not forgive
        them!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  Enter into the rockand hide in the dust  from before the terror
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and from the splendor of his majesty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  The haughty looks of man shall be brought low,and the lofty pride
        of men shall be humbled,and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> alone will be
        exalted in that day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "  For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts has a dayagainst all
        that is proud and lofty,against all that is lifted up\u2014and it shall be
        brought low;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'against all the cedars of Lebanon,lofty and lifted up;and against
        all the oaks of Bashan;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'against all the lofty mountains,and against all the uplifted hills;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'against every high tower,and against every fortified wall;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'against all the ships of Tarshish,and against all the beautiful craft.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  And the haughtiness of man shall be humbled,and the lofty pride
        of men shall be brought low,and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> alone will
        be exalted in that day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  And the idols shall utterly pass away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  And people shall enter the caves of the rocksand the holes of the
        ground,[[COMMENT(0)]]from before the terror of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and
        from the splendor of his majesty,  when he rises to terrify the earth.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:19 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'In that day mankind will cast awaytheir idols of silver and their
        idols of gold,which they made for themselves to worship,to the moles and
        to the bats,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  to enter the caverns of the rocksand the clefts of the cliffs,from
        before the terror of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and from the splendor
        of his majesty,  when he rises to terrify the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  Stop regarding man  in whose nostrils is breath,for of what account
        is he?'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment on Judah and Jerusalem'
      title: Judgment on Judah and Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: '  For behold, the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> of hostsis taking
        away from Jerusalem and from Judahsupport and supply,[[COMMENT(0)]]all support
        of bread,and all support of water;  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:1 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  the mighty man and the soldier,the judge and the prophet,the diviner
        and the elder,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'the captain of fiftyand the man of rank,the counselor and the skillful
        magicianand the expert in charms.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  And I will make boys their princes,and infants[[COMMENT(0)]] shall
        rule over them.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:4 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  And the people will oppress one another,every one his fellowand
        every one his neighbor;the youth will be insolent to the elder,and the despised
        to the honorable.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For a man will take hold of his brotherin the house of his father,
        saying:\u201CYou have a cloak;you shall be our leader,and this heap of ruinsshall
        be under your rule\u201D;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "in that day he will speak out, saying:\u201CI will not be a healer;[[COMMENT(0)]]in
        my house there is neither bread nor cloak;you shall not make meleader of
        the people.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:7 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For Jerusalem has stumbled,and Judah has fallen,because their speech
        and their deeds are against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,  defying his
        glorious presence.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:8 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For the look on their faces bears witness against them;they proclaim
        their sin like Sodom;they do not hide it.Woe to them!  For they have brought
        evil on themselves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  Tell the righteous that it shall be well with them,  for they shall
        eat the fruit of their deeds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  Woe to the wicked! It shall be ill with him,for what his hands
        have dealt out shall be done to him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "My people\u2014infants are their oppressors,and women rule over them.O
        my people, your guides mislead youand they have swallowed up[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the course of your paths.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:12 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  has taken his place to contend;he
        stands to judge peoples.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will enter into judgmentwith the
        elders and princes of his people:\u201CIt is you who have devoured[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the vineyard,  the spoil of the poor is in your houses.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:14 '
        content: Or ; compare Exodus 22:5
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "What do you mean by crushing my people,by grinding the face of the
        poor?\u201Ddeclares the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> of hosts.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said:  Because the daughters of Zion
        are haughtyand walk with outstretched necks,glancing wantonly with their
        eyes,mincing along as they go,  tinkling with their feet,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'therefore the Lord will strike with a scabthe heads of the daughters
        of Zion,and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will lay bare their secret parts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'In that day the Lord will take away the finery of the anklets, the
        headbands, and the crescents; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'the pendants, the bracelets, and the scarves; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'the headdresses, the armlets, the sashes, the perfume boxes, and
        the amulets; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'the signet rings and nose rings; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'the festal robes, the mantles, the cloaks, and the handbags; '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'the mirrors, the linen garments, the turbans, and the veils.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Instead of perfume there will be rottenness;and instead of a belt,
        a rope;and instead of well-set hair, baldness;and instead of a rich robe,
        a skirt of sackcloth;and branding instead of beauty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Your men shall fall by the swordand your mighty men in battle.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: And her gates shall lament and mourn;empty, she shall sit on the ground.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Branch of the  Glorified'
      title: The Branch of the  Glorified
      number: 1
      content: "    And seven women shall take hold of one man in that day, saying,
        \u201CWe will eat our own bread and wear our own clothes, only let us be
        called by your name; take away our reproach.\u201D<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'In that day the branch of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> shall be
        beautiful and glorious, and the fruit of the land shall be the pride and
        honor of the survivors of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And he who is left in Zion and remains in Jerusalem will be called
        holy, everyone who has been recorded for life in Jerusalem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'when the Lord shall have washed away the filth of the daughters of
        Zion and cleansed the bloodstains of Jerusalem from its midst by a spirit
        of judgment and by a spirit of burning.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:4 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will create over the whole site
        of Mount Zion and over her assemblies a cloud by day, and smoke and the shining
        of a flaming fire by night; for over all the glory there will be a canopy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: There will be a booth for shade by day from the heat, and for a refuge
        and a shelter from the storm and rain.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Vineyard of the  Destroyed'
      title: The Vineyard of the  Destroyed
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  Let me sing for my belovedmy love song
        concerning his vineyard:My beloved had a vineyardon a very fertile hill.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He dug it and cleared it of stones,and planted it with choice vines;he
        built a watchtower in the midst of it,and hewed out a wine vat in it;and
        he looked for it to yield grapes,but it yielded wild grapes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And now, O inhabitants of Jerusalemand men of Judah,judge between
        me and my vineyard.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  What more was there to do for my vineyard,that I have not done
        in it?  When I looked for it to yield grapes,why did it yield wild grapes?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And now I will tell youwhat I will do to my vineyard.I will remove
        its hedge,and it shall be devoured;[[COMMENT(0)]]  I will break down its
        wall,and it shall be trampled down.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:5 '
        content: Or ; compare Exodus 22:5
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I will make it a waste;it shall not be pruned or hoed,and briers
        and thorns shall grow up;  I will also command the cloudsthat they rain no
        rain upon it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Woe to the Wicked'
      title: Woe to the Wicked
      number: 7
      content: '  For the vineyard of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hostsis
        the house of Israel,and the men of Judahare his pleasant planting;and he
        looked for justice,but behold, bloodshed;[[COMMENT(0)]]for righteousness,but
        behold, an outcry!  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:7 '
        content: The Hebrew words for and sound alikeThe Hebrew words for and sound
          alike
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Woe to those who join house to house,who add field to field,until
        there is no more room,and you are made to dwell alonein the midst of the
        land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts has sworn in my hearing: 
        \u201CSurely many houses shall be desolate,large and beautiful houses, without
        inhabitant.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "  For ten acres[[COMMENT(0)]] of vineyard shall yield but one bath,and
        a homer of seed shall yield but an ephah.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:10 '
        content: Hebrew , the area ten yoke of oxen can plow in a dayA was about
          6 gallons or 22 liters; a was about 6 bushels or 220 liters; an was about
          3/5 bushel or 22 liters
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Woe to those who rise early in the morning,that they may run after
        strong drink,who tarry late into the eveningas wine inflames them!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  They have lyre and harp,tambourine and flute and wine at their
        feasts,  but they do not regard the deeds of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,or
        see the work of his hands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Therefore my people go into exile  for lack of knowledge;[[COMMENT(0)]]their
        honored men go hungry,and their multitude is parched with thirst.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:13 '
        content: 'Or Or '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore Sheol has enlarged its appetiteand opened its mouth beyond
        measure,and the nobility of Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]] and her multitude will
        go down,her revelers and he who exults in her.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:14 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  Man is humbled, and each one is brought low,and the eyes of the
        haughty[[COMMENT(0)]] are brought low.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:15 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts is exalted[[COMMENT(0)]]
        in justice,and the Holy God shows himself holy in righteousness.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:16 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then shall the lambs graze as in their pasture,and nomads shall eat
        among the ruins of the rich.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Woe to those who draw iniquity with cords of falsehood,who draw sin
        as with cart ropes,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "who say: \u201CLet him be quick,let him speed his workthat we may
        see it;let the counsel of the Holy One of Israel draw near,and let it come,
        that we may know it!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Woe to those who call evil goodand good evil,  who put darkness for
        lightand light for darkness,who put bitter for sweetand sweet for bitter!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Woe to those who are wise in their own eyes,and shrewd in their own
        sight!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Woe to those who are heroes at drinking wine,and valiant men in mixing
        strong drink,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'who acquit the guilty for a bribe,and deprive the innocent of his
        right!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Therefore, as the tongue of fire devours the stubble,and as dry grass
        sinks down in the flame,so their root will be as rottenness,and their blossom
        go up like dust;for they have rejected the law of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts,and have despised the word of the Holy One of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Therefore the anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was kindled
        against his people,and he stretched out his hand against them and struck
        them,and the mountains quaked;and their corpses were as refusein the midst
        of the streets.  For all this his anger has not turned away,and his hand
        is stretched out still.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He will raise a signal for nations far away,and whistle for them
        from the ends of the earth;and behold, quickly, speedily they come!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '  None is weary, none stumbles,none slumbers or sleeps,not a waistband
        is loose,not a sandal strap broken;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "  their arrows are sharp,all their bows bent,their horses\u2019 hoofs
        seem like flint,and their wheels like the whirlwind.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Their roaring is like a lion,like young lions they roar;they growl
        and seize their prey;they carry it off, and none can rescue.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: They will growl over it on that day,like the growling of the sea.And
        if one looks to the land,behold, darkness and distress;and the light is darkened
        by its clouds.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Isaiah\u2019s Vision of the Lord"
      title: "Isaiah\u2019s Vision of the Lord"
      number: 1
      content: '  In the year that King Uzziah died I saw the Lord sitting upon a
        throne, high and lifted up; and the train[[COMMENT(0)]] of his robe filled
        the temple. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:1 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Above him stood the seraphim. Each had six wings: with two he covered
        his face, and with two he covered his feet, and with two he flew. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And one called to another and said:  \u201CHoly, holy, holy is the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts;  the whole earth is full of his glory!\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:3 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the foundations of the thresholds shook at the voice of him who
        called, and the house was filled with smoke. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And I said: \u201CWoe is me! For I am lost; for I am a man of unclean
        lips, and I dwell in the midst of a people of unclean lips; for my eyes have
        seen the King, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then one of the seraphim flew to me, having in his hand a burning
        coal that he had taken with tongs from the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: "7: Isaiah\u2019s Commission from the Lord"
      title: "Isaiah\u2019s Commission from the Lord"
      number: 7
      content: "And he touched my mouth and said: \u201CBehold, this has touched
        your lips; your guilt is taken away, and your sin atoned for.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And I heard the voice of the Lord saying, \u201CWhom shall I send,
        and who will go for us?\u201D Then I said, \u201CHere I am! Send me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And he said, \u201CGo, and say to this people:  \u201C\u2018Keep
        on hearing,[[COMMENT(0)]] but do not understand;keep on seeing, but do not
        perceive.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:9 '
        content: 'Or Or '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "  Make the heart of this people dull,[[COMMENT(0)]]and their ears
        heavy,and blind their eyes;  lest they see with their eyes,and hear with
        their ears,and understand with their hearts,and turn and be healed.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:10 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then I said, \u201CHow long, O Lord?\u201DAnd he said:\u201CUntil
        cities lie wastewithout inhabitant,and houses without people,and the land
        is a desolate waste,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> removes people far away,and the
        forsaken places are many in the midst of the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  And though a tenth remain in it,it will be burned[[COMMENT(0)]]
        again,like a terebinth or an oak,whose stump remainswhen it is felled.\u201D 
        The holy seed is its stump."
      comments:
      - number: '6:13 '
        content: 'Or Or '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Isaiah Sent to King Ahaz'
      title: Isaiah Sent to King Ahaz
      number: 1
      content: '  In the days of Ahaz the son of Jotham, son of Uzziah, king of Judah,
        Rezin the king of Syria and Pekah the son of Remaliah the king of Israel
        came up to Jerusalem to wage war against it, but could not yet mount an attack
        against it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "When the house of David was told, \u201CSyria is in league with[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        Ephraim,\u201D the heart of Ahaz and the heart of his people shook as the
        trees of the forest shake before the wind.  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:2 '
        content: 'Hebrew Hebrew '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Isaiah, \u201CGo out
        to meet Ahaz, you and Shear-jashub[[COMMENT(0)]] your son, at the end of
        the conduit of the upper pool on the highway to the Washer\u2019s Field. "
      comments:
      - number: '7:3 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And say to him, \u2018Be careful, be quiet, do not fear, and do not
        let your heart be faint because of these two smoldering stumps of firebrands,
        at the fierce anger of Rezin and Syria and the son of Remaliah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Because Syria, with Ephraim and the son of Remaliah, has devised
        evil against you, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CLet us go up against Judah and terrify it, and let us conquer
        it[[COMMENT(0)]] for ourselves, and set up the son of Tabeel as king in the
        midst of it,\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '7:6 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "thus says the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>:  \u201C\u2018It shall
        not stand,and it shall not come to pass.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For the head of Syria is Damascus,and the head of Damascus is Rezin.And
        within sixty-five yearsEphraim will be shattered from being a people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: The Sign of Immanuel'
      title: The Sign of Immanuel
      number: 9
      content: "And the head of Ephraim is Samaria,and the head of Samaria is the
        son of Remaliah.  If you[[COMMENT(0)]] are not firm in faith,you will not
        be firm at all.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:9 '
        content: The Hebrew for is plural in verses 9, 13, 14
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Again the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke to Ahaz: '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CAsk a sign of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your[[COMMENT(0)]]
        God; let it be deep as Sheol or high as heaven.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '7:11 '
        content: The Hebrew for and is singular in verses 11, 16, 17
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But Ahaz said, \u201CI will not ask, and I will not put the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        to the test.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And he[[COMMENT(0)]] said, \u201CHear then, O house of David! Is
        it too little for you to weary men, that you weary my God also? "
      comments:
      - number: '7:13 '
        content: That is, Isaiah
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore the Lord himself will give you a sign. Behold, the virgin
        shall conceive and bear a son, and shall call his name Immanuel.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:14 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He shall eat curds and honey when he knows how to refuse the evil
        and choose the good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For before the boy knows how to refuse the evil and choose the good,
        the land whose two kings you dread will be deserted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will bring upon you and upon your
        people and upon your father\u2019s house such days as have not come since
        the day that Ephraim departed from Judah\u2014the king of Assyria!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'In that day the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will whistle for the
        fly that is at the end of the streams of Egypt, and for the bee that is in
        the land of Assyria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And they will all come and settle in the steep ravines, and in the
        clefts of the rocks, and on all the thornbushes, and on all the pastures.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:19 '
        content: 'Or , or '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "In that day the Lord will shave with a razor that is hired beyond
        the River[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014with the king of Assyria\u2014the head and the
        hair of the feet, and it will sweep away the beard also.  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:20 '
        content: That is, the Euphrates
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  In that day a man will keep alive a young cow and two sheep, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'and because of the abundance of milk that they give, he will eat
        curds, for everyone who is left in the land will eat curds and honey.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'In that day every place where there used to be a thousand vines,
        worth a thousand shekels[[COMMENT(0)]] of silver, will become briers and
        thorns. '
      comments:
      - number: '7:23 '
        content: A was about 2/5 ounce or 11 grams
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'With bow and arrows a man will come there, for all the land will
        be briers and thorns. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: And as for all the hills that used to be hoed with a hoe, you will
        not come there for fear of briers and thorns, but they will become a place
        where cattle are let loose and where sheep tread.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Coming Assyrian Invasion'
      title: The Coming Assyrian Invasion
      number: 1
      content: "  Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CTake a large
        tablet and write on it in common characters,[[COMMENT(0)]] \u2018Belonging
        to Maher-shalal-hash-baz.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:1 '
        content: 'Hebrew means '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And I will get reliable witnesses, Uriah the priest and Zechariah
        the son of Jeberechiah, to attest for me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And I went to the prophetess, and she conceived and bore a son. Then
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CCall his name Maher-shalal-hash-baz; "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "for before the boy knows how to cry \u2018My father\u2019 or \u2018My
        mother,\u2019 the wealth of Damascus and the spoil of Samaria will be carried
        away before the king of Assyria.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke to me again: '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CBecause this people has refused the waters of Shiloah that
        flow gently, and rejoice over Rezin and the son of Remaliah, "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'therefore, behold, the Lord is bringing up against them the waters
        of the River,[[COMMENT(0)]] mighty and many, the king of Assyria and all
        his glory. And it will rise over all its channels and go over all its banks, '
      comments:
      - number: '8:7 '
        content: That is, the Euphrates
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "and it will sweep on into Judah, it will overflow and pass on, reaching
        even to the neck, and its outspread wings will fill the breadth of your land,
        O Immanuel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Be broken,[[COMMENT(0)]] you peoples, and be shattered;give ear,
        all you far countries;strap on your armor and be shattered;strap on your
        armor and be shattered.  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:9 '
        content: 'Or Or '
    - name: '10: Fear God, Wait for the '
      title: 'Fear God, Wait for the '
      number: 10
      content: 'Take counsel together, but it will come to nothing;speak a word,
        but it will not stand,for God is with us.[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:10 '
        content: 'The Hebrew for is '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke thus to me with his strong
        hand upon me, and warned me not to walk in the way of this people, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CDo not call conspiracy all that this people calls conspiracy,
        and do not fear what they fear, nor be in dread. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, him you shall honor
        as holy. Let him be your fear, and let him be your dread. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And he will become a sanctuary and a stone of offense and a rock
        of stumbling to both houses of Israel, a trap and a snare to the inhabitants
        of Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And many shall stumble on it. They shall fall and be broken; they
        shall be snared and taken.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Bind up the testimony; seal the teaching[[COMMENT(0)]] among my disciples. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:16 '
        content: Or ; also verse 20
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'I will wait for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, who is hiding his
        face from the house of Jacob, and I will hope in him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Behold, I and the children whom the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has
        given me are signs and portents in Israel from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts, who dwells on Mount Zion. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And when they say to you, \u201CInquire of the mediums and the necromancers
        who chirp and mutter,\u201D should not a people inquire of their God? Should
        they inquire of the dead on behalf of the living? "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'To the teaching and to the testimony! If they will not speak according
        to this word, it is because they have no dawn. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'They will pass through the land,[[COMMENT(0)]] greatly distressed
        and hungry. And when they are hungry, they will be enraged and will speak
        contemptuously against their king and their God, and turn their faces upward. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:21 '
        content: 'Hebrew Or '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: And they will look to the earth, but behold, distress and darkness,
        the gloom of anguish. And they will be thrust into thick darkness.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: For to Us a Child Is Born'
      title: For to Us a Child Is Born
      number: 1
      content: '    [[COMMENT(0)]] But there will be no gloom for her who was in
        anguish. In the former time he brought into contempt the land of Zebulun
        and the land of Naphtali, but in the latter time he has made glorious the
        way of the sea, the land beyond the Jordan, Galilee of the nations.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:1 '
        content: '  Ch 8:23 in Hebrew  Or   '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  [[COMMENT(0)]]  The people who walked in darknesshave seen a great
        light;those who dwelt in a land of deep darkness,on them has light shone.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:2 '
        content: '  Ch 9:1 in Hebrew  '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  You have multiplied the nation;you have increased its joy;they
        rejoice before youas with joy at the harvest,as they are glad when they divide
        the spoil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  For the yoke of his burden,  and the staff for his shoulder,the
        rod of his oppressor,you have broken as on the day of Midian.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  For every boot of the tramping warrior in battle tumultand every
        garment rolled in bloodwill be burned as fuel for the fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  For to us a child is born,to us a son is given;  and the government
        shall be upon[[COMMENT(0)]] his shoulder,and his name shall be calledWonderful
        Counselor, Mighty God,  Everlasting Father, Prince of Peace.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:6 '
        content: 'Or Or '
    - name: '7: Judgment on Arrogance and Oppression'
      title: Judgment on Arrogance and Oppression
      number: 7
      content: 'Of the increase of his government and of peace  there will be no
        end,on the throne of David and over his kingdom,to establish it and to uphold
        it  with justice and with righteousnessfrom this time forth and forevermore. 
        The zeal of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts will do this.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The Lord has sent a word against Jacob,and it will fall on Israel;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'and all the people will know,  Ephraim and the inhabitants of Samaria,who
        say in pride and in arrogance of heart:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThe bricks have fallen,but we will build with dressed stones;the
        sycamores have been cut down,but we will put cedars in their place.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> raises the adversaries of Rezin
        against him,and stirs up his enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  The Syrians on the east and the Philistines on the westdevour Israel
        with open mouth.  For all this his anger has not turned away,and his hand
        is stretched out still.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The people did not turn to him who struck them,nor inquire of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> cut off from Israel head and tail,palm
        branch and reed in one day\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  the elder and honored man is the head,and the prophet who teaches
        lies is the tail;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'for those who guide this people have been leading them astray,and
        those who are guided by them are swallowed up.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Therefore the Lord does not rejoice over their young men,and has
        no compassion on their fatherless and widows;for everyone is godless and
        an evildoer,and every mouth speaks folly.[[COMMENT(0)]]  For all this his
        anger has not turned away,and his hand is stretched out still.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:17 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For wickedness burns like a fire;it consumes briers and thorns;it
        kindles the thickets of the forest,and they roll upward in a column of smoke.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Through the wrath of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hoststhe
        land is scorched,and the people are like fuel for the fire;  no one spares
        another.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  They slice meat on the right, but are still hungry,and they devour
        on the left, but are not satisfied;  each devours the flesh of his own arm,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Manasseh devours Ephraim, and Ephraim devours Manasseh;together they
        are against Judah.  For all this his anger has not turned away,and his hand
        is stretched out still.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  Woe to those who decree iniquitous decrees,and the writers who
        keep writing oppression,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'to turn aside the needy from justiceand to rob the poor of my people
        of their right,that widows may be their spoil,and that they may make the
        fatherless their prey!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'What will you do on the day of punishment,in the ruin that will come
        from afar?To whom will you flee for help,and where will you leave your wealth?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Judgment on Arrogant Assyria'
      title: Judgment on Arrogant Assyria
      number: 4
      content: 'Nothing remains but to crouch among the prisonersor fall among the
        slain.  For all this his anger has not turned away,and his hand is stretched
        out still.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Woe to Assyria, the rod of my anger;the staff in their hands is my
        fury!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Against a godless nation I send him,and against the people of my
        wrath I command him,to take spoil and seize plunder,and to tread them down
        like the mire of the streets.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But he does not so intend,and his heart does not so think;but it
        is in his heart to destroy,and to cut off nations not a few;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "for he says:  \u201CAre not my commanders all kings?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  Is not Calno like Carchemish?Is not Hamath like Arpad?  Is not
        Samaria like Damascus?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'As my hand has reached to the kingdoms of the idols,whose carved
        images were greater than those of Jerusalem and Samaria,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "shall I not do to Jerusalem and her idols  as I have done to Samaria
        and her images?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  When the Lord has finished all his work on Mount Zion and on Jerusalem,
        he[[COMMENT(0)]] will punish the speech of the arrogant heart of the king
        of Assyria and the boastful look in his eyes. '
      comments:
      - number: '10:12 '
        content: 'Hebrew Hebrew '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "For he says:\u201CBy the strength of my hand I have done it,and by
        my wisdom, for I have understanding;I remove the boundaries of peoples,and
        plunder their treasures;like a bull I bring down those who sit on thrones.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "My hand has found like a nestthe wealth of the peoples;and as one
        gathers eggs that have been forsaken,so I have gathered all the earth;and
        there was none that moved a wingor opened the mouth or chirped.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Shall the axe boast over him who hews with it,or the saw magnify
        itself against him who wields it?As if a rod should wield him who lifts it,or
        as if a staff should lift him who is not wood!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Therefore the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> of hostswill send wasting
        sickness among his stout warriors,and under his glory a burning will be kindled,like
        the burning of fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  The light of Israel will become a fire,and his Holy One a flame,and
        it will burn and devourhis thorns and briers in one day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The glory of his forest and of his fruitful landthe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will destroy, both soul and body,and it will be as when a sick man wastes
        away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: The Remnant of Israel Will Return'
      title: The Remnant of Israel Will Return
      number: 19
      content: 'The remnant of the trees of his forest will be so fewthat a child
        can write them down.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  In that day the remnant of Israel and the survivors of the house
        of Jacob will no more lean on him who struck them, but will lean on the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the Holy One of Israel, in truth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'A remnant will return, the remnant of Jacob, to the mighty God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For though your people Israel be as the sand of the sea, only a remnant
        of them will return. Destruction is decreed, overflowing with righteousness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> of hosts will make a full
        end, as decreed, in the midst of all the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> of hosts:
        \u201CO my people, who dwell in Zion, be not afraid of the Assyrians when
        they strike with the rod and lift up their staff against you as the Egyptians
        did. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'For in a very little while my fury will come to an end, and my anger
        will be directed to their destruction. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts will wield against them
        a whip, as when he struck Midian at the rock of Oreb. And his staff will
        be over the sea, and he will lift it as he did in Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And in that day his burden will depart from your shoulder, and his
        yoke from your neck; and the yoke will be broken because of the fat.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:27 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'He has come to Aiath;he has passed through Migron;at Michmash he
        stores his baggage;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'they have crossed over the pass;at Geba they lodge for the night; 
        Ramah trembles;  Gibeah of Saul has fled.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Cry aloud, O daughter of Gallim!Give attention, O Laishah!O poor
        Anathoth!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Madmenah is in flight;the inhabitants of Gebim flee for safety.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'This very day he will halt at Nob;he will shake his fistat the mount
        of the daughter of Zion,the hill of Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Behold, the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> of hosts  will lop the
        boughs with terrifying power;the great in height will be hewn down,and the
        lofty will be brought low.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: He will cut down the thickets of the forest with an axe,and Lebanon
        will fall by the Majestic One.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Righteous Reign of the Branch'
      title: The Righteous Reign of the Branch
      number: 1
      content: '  There shall come forth a shoot from the stump of Jesse,and a branch
        from his roots shall bear fruit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the Spirit of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> shall rest upon
        him,the Spirit of wisdom and understanding,the Spirit of counsel and might,the
        Spirit of knowledge and the fear of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And his delight shall be in the fear of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. 
        He shall not judge by what his eyes see,or decide disputes by what his ears
        hear,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'but with righteousness he shall judge the poor,and decide with equity
        for the meek of the earth;and he shall strike the earth with the rod of his
        mouth,and with the breath of his lips he shall kill the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Righteousness shall be the belt of his waist,and faithfulness the
        belt of his loins.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  The wolf shall dwell with the lamb,and the leopard shall lie down
        with the young goat,and the calf and the lion and the fattened calf together;and
        a little child shall lead them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The cow and the bear shall graze;their young shall lie down together;and
        the lion shall eat straw like the ox.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The nursing child shall play over the hole of the cobra,and the weaned
        child shall put his hand on the adder\u2019s den.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  They shall not hurt or destroyin all my holy mountain;  for the
        earth shall be full of the knowledge of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>as
        the waters cover the sea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "In that day the root of Jesse, who shall stand as a signal for the
        peoples\u2014of him shall the nations inquire, and his resting place shall
        be glorious.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  In that day the Lord will extend his hand yet a second time to
        recover the remnant that remains of his people, from Assyria, from Egypt,
        from Pathros, from Cush,[[COMMENT(0)]] from Elam, from Shinar, from Hamath,
        and from the coastlands of the sea.  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:11 '
        content: 'Probably '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He will raise a signal for the nationsand will assemble the banished
        of Israel,and gather the dispersed of Judahfrom the four corners of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  The jealousy of Ephraim shall depart,and those who harass Judah
        shall be cut off;Ephraim shall not be jealous of Judah,and Judah shall not
        harass Ephraim.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  But they shall swoop down on the shoulder of the Philistines in
        the west,and together they shall plunder the people of the east.They shall
        put out their hand against Edom and Moab,and the Ammonites shall obey them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will utterly destroy[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        the tongue of the Sea of Egypt,and will wave his hand over the Riverwith
        his scorching breath,and strike it into seven channels,and he will lead people
        across in sandals.  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:15 '
        content: 'Hebrew That is, the EuphratesOr '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: And there will be a highway from Assyriafor the remnant that remains
        of his people,  as there was for Israelwhen they came up from the land of
        Egypt.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The  Is My Strength and My Song'
      title: The  Is My Strength and My Song
      number: 1
      content: "<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  You[[COMMENT(0)]] will say in that day:\u201CI
        will give thanks to you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,for though you were
        angry with me,  your anger turned away,that you might comfort me.  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:1 '
        content: The Hebrew for is singular in verse 1
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CBehold, God is my salvation;I will trust, and will not be afraid;for
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>[[COMMENT(0)]]
        is my strength and my song,and he has become my salvation.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:2 '
        content: 'Hebrew <span class="ChapterContent_bdit___RrVH">Lord</span>  '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  With joy you[[COMMENT(0)]] will draw water from the wells of salvation. '
      comments:
      - number: '12:3 '
        content: The Hebrew for is plural in verses 3, 4
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And you will say in that day:  \u201CGive thanks to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,call
        upon his name,  make known his deeds among the peoples,proclaim that his
        name is exalted.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "  \u201CSing praises to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, for he has
        done gloriously;let this be made known[[COMMENT(0)]] in all the earth.  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:5 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Shout, and sing for joy, O inhabitant of Zion,for great in your[[COMMENT(0)]]
        midst is the Holy One of Israel.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '12:6 '
        content: 'The Hebrew for in verse 6 is singular, referring to the '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Judgment of Babylon'
      title: The Judgment of Babylon
      number: 1
      content: '  The oracle concerning Babylon which Isaiah the son of Amoz saw.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'On a bare hill raise a signal;cry aloud to them;wave the hand for
        them to enterthe gates of the nobles.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I myself have commanded my consecrated ones,and have summoned my
        mighty men to execute my anger,my proudly exulting ones.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:3 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The sound of a tumult is on the mountainsas of a great multitude!The
        sound of an uproar of kingdoms,of nations gathering together!  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts is musteringa host for battle.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  They come from a distant land,from the end of the heavens,the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and the weapons of his indignation,to destroy the whole land.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:5 '
        content: Or ; also verse 9
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  Wail, for the day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is near;as
        destruction from the Almighty[[COMMENT(0)]] it will come!  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:6 '
        content: The Hebrew words for and sound alike
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Therefore all hands will be feeble,and every human heart will melt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They will be dismayed:  pangs and agony will seize them;  they will
        be in anguish like a woman in labor.They will look aghast at one another;their
        faces will be aflame.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Behold, the day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> comes,cruel, with
        wrath and fierce anger,to make the land a desolationand to destroy its sinners
        from it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  For the stars of the heavens and their constellationswill not give
        their light;  the sun will be dark at its rising,and the moon will not shed
        its light.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'I will punish the world for its evil,and the wicked for their iniquity;I
        will put an end to the pomp of the arrogant,  and lay low the pompous pride
        of the ruthless.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I will make people more rare than fine gold,and mankind than the
        gold of Ophir.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Therefore I will make the heavens tremble,and the earth will be shaken
        out of its place,at the wrath of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hostsin
        the day of his fierce anger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And like a hunted gazelle,or like sheep with none to gather them, 
        each will turn to his own people,and each will flee to his own land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Whoever is found will be thrust through,and whoever is caught will
        fall by the sword.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  Their infants will be dashed in piecesbefore their eyes;their houses
        will be plunderedand their wives ravished.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Behold, I am stirring up the Medes against them,who have no regard
        for silverand do not delight in gold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  Their bows will slaughter[[COMMENT(0)]] the young men;they will
        have no mercy on the fruit of the womb;their eyes will not pity children.  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:18 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And Babylon, the glory of kingdoms,the splendor and pomp of the Chaldeans,will
        be like Sodom and Gomorrahwhen God overthrew them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  It will never be inhabitedor lived in for all generations;no Arab
        will pitch his tent there;no shepherds will make their flocks lie down there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But wild animals will lie down there,and their houses will be full
        of howling creatures;there ostriches[[COMMENT(0)]] will dwell,and there wild
        goats will dance.  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:21 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Hyenas[[COMMENT(0)]] will cry in its towers,and jackals in the pleasant
        palaces;its time is close at handand its days will not be prolonged.
      comments:
      - number: '13:22 '
        content: 'Or '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Restoration of Jacob'
      title: The Restoration of Jacob
      number: 1
      content: '    For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will have compassion on Jacob
        and will again choose Israel, and will set them in their own land, and sojourners
        will join them and will attach themselves to the house of Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: "2: Israel\u2019s Remnant Taunts Babylon"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Remnant Taunts Babylon"
      number: 2
      content: "And the peoples will take them and bring them to their place, and
        the house of Israel will possess them in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        land as male and female slaves.[[COMMENT(0)]]  They will take captive those
        who were their captors, and rule over those who oppressed them.  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:2 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has given you rest from your
        pain and turmoil and the hard service with which you were made to serve, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "you will take up this taunt against the king of Babylon:\u201CHow
        the oppressor has ceased,  the insolent fury[[COMMENT(0)]] ceased!  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:4 '
        content: Dead Sea Scroll (compare Septuagint, Syriac, Vulgate); the meaning
          of the word in the Masoretic Text is uncertain
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has broken the staff of the wicked,the
        scepter of rulers,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  that struck the peoples in wrathwith unceasing blows,that ruled
        the nations in angerwith unrelenting persecution.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The whole earth is at rest and quiet;  they break forth into singing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "    The cypresses rejoice at you,  the cedars of Lebanon, saying,\u2018Since
        you were laid low,no woodcutter comes up against us.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Sheol beneath is stirred upto meet you when you come;it rouses the
        shades to greet you,all who were leaders of the earth;it raises from their
        thronesall who were kings of the nations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "  All of them will answerand say to you:\u2018You too have become
        as weak as we!You have become like us!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Your pomp is brought down to Sheol,the sound of your harps;maggots
        are laid as a bed beneath you,and worms are your covers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CHow you are fallen from heaven,O Day Star, son of Dawn!How
        you are cut down to the ground,you who laid the nations low!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "You said in your heart,  \u2018I will ascend to heaven;above the
        stars of God  I will set my throne on high;I will sit on the mount of assemblyin
        the far reaches of the north;[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:13 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "I will ascend above the heights of the clouds;I will make myself
        like the Most High.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  But you are brought down to Sheol,to the far reaches of the pit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Those who see you will stare at youand ponder over you:\u2018Is this
        the man who made the earth tremble,who shook kingdoms,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "who made the world like a desertand overthrew its cities,  who did
        not let his prisoners go home?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'All the kings of the nations lie in glory,each in his own tomb;[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:18 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'but you are cast out, away from your grave,like a loathed branch, 
        clothed with the slain, those pierced by the sword,who go down to the stones
        of the pit,like a dead body trampled underfoot.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "You will not be joined with them in burial,because you have destroyed
        your land,you have slain your people.\u201CMay the offspring of evildoersnevermore
        be named!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Prepare slaughter for his sons  because of the guilt of their fathers,lest
        they rise and possess the earth,and fill the face of the world with cities.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CI will rise up against them,\u201D declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts, \u201Cand will cut off from Babylon name and remnant, descendants
        and posterity,\u201D declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: An Oracle Concerning Assyria'
      title: An Oracle Concerning Assyria
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CAnd I will make it a possession of the hedgehog,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and pools of water, and I will sweep it with the broom of destruction,\u201D
        declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts.  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:23 '
        content: 'Possibly , or '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts has sworn:  \u201CAs I have
        planned,so shall it be,and as I have purposed,so shall it stand,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "that I will break the Assyrian in my land,and on my mountains trample
        him underfoot;and his yoke shall depart from them,and his burden from their
        shoulder.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'This is the purpose that is purposedconcerning the whole earth,and
        this is the hand that is stretched outover all the nations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: An Oracle Concerning Philistia'
      title: An Oracle Concerning Philistia
      number: 27
      content: '  For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts has purposed,and who
        will annul it?  His hand is stretched out,and who will turn it back?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'In the year that King Ahaz died came this oracle:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Rejoice not, O Philistia, all of you,that the rod that struck you
        is broken,for from the serpent\u2019s root will come forth an adder,and its
        fruit will be a flying fiery serpent.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And the firstborn of the poor will graze,and the needy lie down in
        safety;but I will kill your root with famine,and your remnant it will slay.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: '  Wail, O gate; cry out, O city;melt in fear, O Philistia, all of
        you!  For smoke comes out of the north,and there is no straggler in his ranks.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "What will one answer the messengers of the nation?  \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has founded Zion,and in her the afflicted of his people find refuge.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: An Oracle Concerning Moab'
      title: An Oracle Concerning Moab
      number: 1
      content: '  An oracle concerning Moab.Because Ar of Moab is laid waste in a
        night,Moab is undone;because Kir of Moab is laid waste in a night,Moab is
        undone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He has gone up to the temple,[[COMMENT(0)]] and to Dibon,to the high
        places to weep;over Nebo and over MedebaMoab wails.On every head is baldness;every
        beard is shorn;  '
      comments:
      - number: '15:2 '
        content: 'Hebrew Or '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'in the streets they wear sackcloth;on the housetops and in the squareseveryone
        wails and melts in tears.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  Heshbon and Elealeh cry out;their voice is heard as far as Jahaz;therefore
        the armed men of Moab cry aloud;his soul trembles.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'My heart cries out for Moab;her fugitives flee to Zoar,to Eglath-shelishiyah.For
        at the ascent of Luhiththey go up weeping;on the road to Horonaimthey raise
        a cry of destruction;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'the waters of Nimrimare a desolation;the grass is withered, the vegetation
        fails,the greenery is no more.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  Therefore the abundance they have gainedand what they have laid
        upthey carry awayover the Brook of the Willows.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For a cry has gonearound the land of Moab;her wailing reaches to
        Eglaim;her wailing reaches to Beer-elim.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: For the waters of Dibon[[COMMENT(0)]] are full of blood;for I will
        bring upon Dibon even more,  a lion for those of Moab who escape,for the
        remnant of the land.
      comments:
      - number: '15:9 '
        content: Dead Sea Scroll, Vulgate (compare Syriac); Masoretic Text ; twice
          in this verse
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '    Send the lamb to the ruler of the land,from Sela, by way of the
        desert,to the mount of the daughter of Zion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Like fleeing birds,like a scattered nest,so are the daughters of
        Moabat the fords of the Arnon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CGive counsel;grant justice;  make your shade like nightat the
        height of noon;shelter the outcasts;do not reveal the fugitive;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'let the outcasts of Moabsojourn among you;be a shelter to them[[COMMENT(0)]]from
        the destroyer.When the oppressor is no more,and destruction has ceased,and
        he who tramples underfoot has vanished from the land,  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:4 '
        content: 'Some Hebrew manuscripts, Septuagint, Syriac; Masoretic Text '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "  then a throne will be established in steadfast love,and on it will
        sit in faithfulnessin the tent of Davidone who judges and seeks justiceand
        is swift to do righteousness.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "  We have heard of the pride of Moab\u2014how proud he is!\u2014 
        of his arrogance, his pride, and his insolence;in his idle boasting he is
        not right.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Therefore let Moab wail for Moab,  let everyone wail.Mourn, utterly
        stricken,for the raisin cakes of Kir-hareseth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For the fields of Heshbon languish,and the vine of Sibmah;the lords
        of the nationshave struck down its branches,which reached to Jazerand strayed
        to the desert;its shoots spread abroadand passed over the sea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Therefore I weep with the weeping of Jazerfor the vine of Sibmah;I
        drench you with my tears,O Heshbon and Elealeh;for over your summer fruit
        and your harvestthe shout has ceased.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  And joy and gladness are taken away from the fruitful field,and
        in the vineyards no songs are sung,no cheers are raised;no treader treads
        out wine in the presses;I have put an end to the shouting.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Therefore my inner parts moan like a lyre for Moab,and my inmost
        self for Kir-hareseth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And when Moab presents himself, when he wearies himself on the high
        place, when he comes to his sanctuary to pray, he will not prevail.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'This is the word that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke concerning
        Moab in the past. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But now the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has spoken, saying, \u201CIn
        three years, like the years of a hired worker, the glory of Moab will be
        brought into contempt, in spite of all his great multitude, and those who
        remain will be very few and feeble.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: An Oracle Concerning Damascus'
      title: An Oracle Concerning Damascus
      number: 1
      content: '  An oracle concerning Damascus.Behold, Damascus will cease to be
        a cityand will become a heap of ruins.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The cities of Aroer are deserted;they will be for flocks,which will
        lie down, and none will make them afraid.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The fortress will disappear from Ephraim,and the kingdom from Damascus;and
        the remnant of Syria will belike the glory of the children of Israel,declares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And in that day the glory of Jacob will be brought low,and the fat
        of his flesh will grow lean.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And it shall be as when the reaper gathers standing grainand his
        arm harvests the ears,and as when one gleans the ears of grainin the Valley
        of Rephaim.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "  Gleanings will be left in it,as when an olive tree is beaten\u2014two
        or three berriesin the top of the highest bough,four or fiveon the branches
        of a fruit tree,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  In that day man will look to his Maker, and his eyes will look
        on the Holy One of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He will not look to the altars, the work of his hands, and he will
        not look on what his own fingers have made, either the Asherim or the altars
        of incense.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  In that day their strong cities will be like the deserted places
        of the wooded heights and the hilltops, which they deserted because of the
        children of Israel, and there will be desolation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For you have forgotten the God of your salvationand have not remembered
        the Rock of your refuge;therefore, though you plant pleasant plantsand sow
        the vine-branch of a stranger,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'though you make them grow[[COMMENT(0)]] on the day that you plant
        them,and make them blossom in the morning that you sow,yet the harvest will
        flee awayin a day of grief and incurable pain.  '
      comments:
      - number: '17:11 '
        content: 'Or Or '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Ah, the thunder of many peoples;they thunder like the thundering
        of the sea!Ah, the roar of nations;they roar like the roaring of mighty waters!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  The nations roar like the roaring of many waters,  but he will
        rebuke them, and they will flee far away,chased like chaff on the mountains
        before the windand whirling dust before the storm.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  At evening time, behold, terror!Before morning, they are no more!This
        is the portion of those who loot us,and the lot of those who plunder us.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: An Oracle Concerning Cush'
      title: An Oracle Concerning Cush
      number: 1
      content: '  Ah, land of whirring wingsthat is beyond the rivers of Cush,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '18:1 '
        content: 'Probably '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'which sends ambassadors by the sea,in vessels of papyrus on the waters!Go,
        you swift messengers,to a nation tall and smooth,to a people feared near
        and far,a nation mighty and conquering,whose land the rivers divide.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'All you inhabitants of the world,you who dwell on the earth,when
        a signal is raised on the mountains, look!When a trumpet is blown, hear!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For thus the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me:\u201CI will
        quietly look from my dwellinglike clear heat in sunshine,like a cloud of
        dew in the heat of harvest.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  For before the harvest, when the blossom is over,and the flower
        becomes a ripening grape,he cuts off the shoots with pruning hooks,and the
        spreading branches he lops off and clears away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  They shall all of them be leftto the birds of prey of the mountainsand
        to the beasts of the earth.And the birds of prey will summer on them,and
        all the beasts of the earth will winter on them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  At that time tribute will be brought to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hostsfrom a people tall and smooth,from a people feared near and far,a
        nation mighty and conquering,whose land the rivers divide,to Mount Zion,
        the place of the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: An Oracle Concerning Egypt'
      title: An Oracle Concerning Egypt
      number: 1
      content: '  An oracle concerning Egypt.Behold, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        is riding on a swift cloudand comes to Egypt;and the idols of Egypt will
        tremble at his presence,and the heart of the Egyptians will melt within them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And I will stir up Egyptians against Egyptians,  and they will fight,
        each against anotherand each against his neighbor,city against city, kingdom
        against kingdom;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and the spirit of the Egyptians within them will be emptied out,and
        I will confound[[COMMENT(0)]] their counsel;and they will inquire of the
        idols and the sorcerers,and the mediums and the necromancers;  '
      comments:
      - number: '19:3 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and I will give over the Egyptiansinto the hand of a hard master,and
        a fierce king will rule over them,declares the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>
        of hosts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the waters of the sea will be dried up,and the river will be
        dry and parched,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "and its canals will become foul,and the branches of Egypt\u2019s
        Nile will diminish and dry up,reeds and rushes will rot away.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'There will be bare places by the Nile,on the brink of the Nile,and
        all that is sown by the Nile will be parched,will be driven away, and will
        be no more.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The fishermen will mourn and lament,all who cast a hook in the Nile;and
        they will languishwho spread nets on the water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The workers in combed flax will be in despair,and the weavers of
        white cotton.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Those who are the pillars of the land will be crushed,and all who
        work for pay will be grieved.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The princes of Zoan are utterly foolish;the wisest counselors of
        Pharaoh give stupid counsel.How can you say to Pharaoh,\u201CI am a son of
        the wise,a son of ancient kings\u201D?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Where then are your wise men?Let them tell youthat they might know
        what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts has purposed against Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The princes of Zoan have become fools,and the princes of Memphis
        are deluded;those who are the cornerstones of her tribeshave made Egypt stagger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has mingled within her a spirit of
        confusion,and they will make Egypt stagger in all its deeds,  as a drunken
        man staggers in his vomit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Egypt, Assyria, Israel Blessed'
      title: Egypt, Assyria, Israel Blessed
      number: 15
      content: 'And there will be nothing for Egyptthat head or tail, palm branch
        or reed, may do.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'In that day the Egyptians will be like women, and tremble with fear
        before the hand that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts shakes over
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the land of Judah will become a terror to the Egyptians. Everyone
        to whom it is mentioned will fear because of the purpose that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts has purposed against them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  In that day there will be five cities in the land of Egypt that
        speak the language of Canaan and swear allegiance to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts. One of these will be called the City of Destruction.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '19:18 '
        content: 'Dead Sea Scroll and some other manuscripts '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'In that day there will be an altar to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        in the midst of the land of Egypt, and a pillar to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        at its border. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'It will be a sign and a witness to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts in the land of Egypt. When they cry to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        because of oppressors, he will send them a savior and defender, and deliver
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will make himself known to the
        Egyptians, and the Egyptians will know the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> in
        that day and worship with sacrifice and offering, and they will make vows
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and perform them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will strike Egypt, striking and
        healing, and they will return to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and he
        will listen to their pleas for mercy and heal them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  In that day there will be a highway from Egypt to Assyria, and
        Assyria will come into Egypt, and Egypt into Assyria, and the Egyptians will
        worship with the Assyrians.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'In that day Israel will be the third with Egypt and Assyria, a blessing
        in the midst of the earth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "whom the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts has blessed, saying,
        \u201CBlessed be Egypt my people, and Assyria the work of my hands, and Israel
        my inheritance.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Sign Against Egypt and Cush'
      title: A Sign Against Egypt and Cush
      number: 1
      content: "  In the year that the commander in chief, who was sent by Sargon
        the king of Assyria, came to Ashdod and fought against it and captured it\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "at that time the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke by Isaiah the
        son of Amoz, saying, \u201CGo, and loose the sackcloth from your waist and
        take off your sandals from your feet,\u201D and he did so, walking naked
        and barefoot.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CAs my servant Isaiah
        has walked naked and barefoot for three years as a sign and a portent against
        Egypt and Cush,[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '20:3 '
        content: 'Probably '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'so shall the king of Assyria lead away the Egyptian captives and
        the Cushite exiles, both the young and the old, naked and barefoot, with
        buttocks uncovered, the nakedness of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then they shall be dismayed and ashamed because of Cush their hope
        and of Egypt their boast. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the inhabitants of this coastland will say in that day, \u2018Behold,
        this is what has happened to those in whom we hoped and to whom we fled for
        help to be delivered from the king of Assyria! And we, how shall we escape?\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Fallen, Fallen Is Babylon'
      title: Fallen, Fallen Is Babylon
      number: 1
      content: '  The oracle concerning the wilderness of the sea.  As whirlwinds
        in the Negeb sweep on,it comes from the wilderness,from a terrible land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'A stern vision is told to me;  the traitor betrays,and the destroyer
        destroys.Go up, O Elam;lay siege, O Media;all the sighing she has causedI
        bring to an end.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore my loins are filled with anguish;  pangs have seized me,like
        the pangs of a woman in labor;I am bowed down so that I cannot hear;I am
        dismayed so that I cannot see.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'My heart staggers; horror has appalled me;  the twilight I longed
        forhas been turned for me into trembling.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  They prepare the table,they spread the rugs,[[COMMENT(0)]]they
        eat, they drink.Arise, O princes;  oil the shield!  '
      comments:
      - number: '21:5 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For thus the Lord said to me:\u201CGo, set a watchman;let him announce
        what he sees.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When he sees riders, horsemen in pairs,riders on donkeys, riders
        on camels,let him listen diligently,very diligently.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then he who saw cried out:[[COMMENT(0)]]  \u201CUpon a watchtower
        I stand, O Lord,continually by day,and at my post I am stationedwhole nights.  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:8 '
        content: 'Dead Sea Scroll, Syriac; Masoretic Text , or '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And behold, here come riders,horsemen in pairs!\u201D  And he answered, 
        \u201CFallen, fallen is Babylon;  and all the carved images of her godshe
        has shattered to the ground.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'O my threshed and winnowed one,what I have heard from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts,the God of Israel, I announce to you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The oracle concerning Dumah.One is calling to me from Seir,\u201CWatchman,
        what time of the night?Watchman, what time of the night?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The watchman says:\u201CMorning comes, and also the night.If you
        will inquire, inquire;come back again.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The oracle concerning Arabia.In the thickets in Arabia you will lodge,O
        caravans of Dedanites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'To the thirsty bring water;meet the fugitive with bread,O inhabitants
        of the land of Tema.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For they have fled from the swords,from the drawn sword,from the
        bent bow,and from the press of battle.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "For thus the Lord said to me, \u201CWithin a year, according to the
        years of a hired worker, all the glory of Kedar will come to an end. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And the remainder of the archers of the mighty men of the sons of
        Kedar will be few, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel,
        has spoken.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: An Oracle Concerning Jerusalem'
      title: An Oracle Concerning Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: '  The oracle concerning the valley of vision.What do you mean that
        you have gone up,all of you, to the housetops,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'you who are full of shoutings,tumultuous city, exultant town?Your
        slain are not slain with the swordor dead in battle.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  All your leaders have fled together;without the bow they were captured.All
        of you who were found were captured,though they had fled far away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Therefore I said:\u201CLook away from me;  let me weep bitter tears;do
        not labor to comfort meconcerning the destruction of the daughter of my people.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  For the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> of hosts has a dayof tumult
        and trampling and confusionin the valley of vision,a battering down of wallsand
        a shouting to the mountains.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Elam bore the quiverwith chariots and horsemen,and Kir uncovered
        the shield.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Your choicest valleys were full of chariots,and the horsemen took
        their stand at the gates.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He has taken away the covering of Judah.In that day you looked to
        the weapons of the House of the Forest, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'and you saw that the breaches of the city of David were many. You
        collected the waters of the lower pool, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and you counted the houses of Jerusalem, and you broke down the houses
        to fortify the wall. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'You made a reservoir between the two walls for the water of the old
        pool. But you did not look to him who did it, or see him who planned it long
        ago.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'In that day the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> of hostscalled for
        weeping and mourning,for baldness and wearing sackcloth;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "and behold, joy and gladness,killing oxen and slaughtering sheep,eating
        flesh and drinking wine.  \u201CLet us eat and drink,for tomorrow we die.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts has revealed himself in
        my ears:\u201CSurely this iniquity will not be atoned for you until you die,\u201Dsays
        the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> of hosts.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Thus says the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> of hosts, \u201CCome,
        go to this steward, to Shebna, who is over the household, and say to him: "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'What have you to do here, and whom have you here, that you have cut
        out here a tomb for yourself, you who cut out a tomb on the height and carve
        a dwelling for yourself in the rock? '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Behold, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will hurl you away violently,
        O you strong man. He will seize firm hold on you '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "and whirl you around and around, and throw you like a ball into a
        wide land. There you shall die, and there shall be your glorious chariots,
        you shame of your master\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'I will thrust you from your office, and you will be pulled down from
        your station. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'In that day I will call my servant Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'and I will clothe him with your robe, and will bind your sash on
        him, and will commit your authority to his hand. And he shall be a father
        to the inhabitants of Jerusalem and to the house of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And I will place on his shoulder the key of the house of David. He
        shall open, and none shall shut; and he shall shut, and none shall open. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And I will fasten him like a peg in a secure place, and he will become
        a throne of honor to his father\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And they will hang on him the whole honor of his father\u2019s house,
        the offspring and issue, every small vessel, from the cups to all the flagons. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "In that day, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the
        peg that was fastened in a secure place will give way, and it will be cut
        down and fall, and the load that was on it will be cut off, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has spoken.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: An Oracle Concerning Tyre and Sidon'
      title: An Oracle Concerning Tyre and Sidon
      number: 1
      content: '  The oracle concerning Tyre.Wail, O ships of Tarshish,for Tyre is
        laid waste, without house or harbor!From the land of Cyprus[[COMMENT(0)]]it
        is revealed to them.  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:1 '
        content: Hebrew ; also verse 12
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Be still, O inhabitants of the coast;the merchants of Sidon, who
        cross the sea, have filled you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And on many watersyour revenue was the grain of Shihor,the harvest
        of the Nile;you were the merchant of the nations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Be ashamed, O Sidon, for the sea has spoken,the stronghold of the
        sea, saying:\u201CI have neither labored nor given birth,I have neither reared
        young mennor brought up young women.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When the report comes to Egypt,they will be in anguish[[COMMENT(0)]]
        over the report about Tyre.  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:5 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  Cross over to Tarshish;wail, O inhabitants of the coast!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Is this your exultant city  whose origin is from days of old,whose
        feet carried herto settle far away?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Who has purposed thisagainst Tyre, the bestower of crowns,whose merchants
        were princes,whose traders were the honored of the earth?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts has purposed it,  to defile
        the pompous pride of all glory,[[COMMENT(0)]]to dishonor all the honored
        of the earth.  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:9 '
        content: The Hebrew words for and sound alike
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Cross over your land like the Nile,O daughter of Tarshish;there is
        no restraint anymore.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  He has stretched out his hand over the sea;he has shaken the kingdoms;the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has given command concerning Canaanto destroy
        its strongholds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And he said:\u201CYou will no more exult,O oppressed virgin daughter
        of Sidon;arise, cross over to Cyprus,even there you will have no rest.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Behold the land of the Chaldeans! This is the people that was not;[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Assyria destined it for wild beasts. They erected their siege towers, they
        stripped her palaces bare, they made her a ruin.  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:13 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  Wail, O ships of Tarshish,for your stronghold is laid waste.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'In that day Tyre will be forgotten for seventy years, like the days[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of one king. At the end of seventy years, it will happen to Tyre as in the
        song of the prostitute:  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:15 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CTake a harp;go about the city,O forgotten prostitute!Make sweet
        melody;sing many songs,that you may be remembered.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'At the end of seventy years, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will
        visit Tyre, and she will return to her wages and will prostitute herself
        with all the kingdoms of the world on the face of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Her merchandise and her wages will be holy to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        It will not be stored or hoarded, but her merchandise will supply abundant
        food and fine clothing for those who dwell before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment on the Whole Earth'
      title: Judgment on the Whole Earth
      number: 1
      content: '  Behold, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will empty the earth[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and make it desolate,and he will twist its surface and scatter its inhabitants.  '
      comments:
      - number: '24:1 '
        content: Or ; also throughout this chapter
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  And it shall be, as with the people, so with the priest;as with
        the slave, so with his master;as with the maid, so with her mistress;  as
        with the buyer, so with the seller;as with the lender, so with the borrower; 
        as with the creditor, so with the debtor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  The earth shall be utterly empty and utterly plundered;  for the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has spoken this word.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  The earth mourns and withers;the world languishes and withers;the
        highest people of the earth languish.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The earth lies defiledunder its inhabitants;for they have transgressed
        the laws,violated the statutes,broken the everlasting covenant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Therefore a curse devours the earth,and its inhabitants suffer for
        their guilt;therefore the inhabitants of the earth are scorched,and few men
        are left.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  The wine mourns,the vine languishes,all the merry-hearted sigh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  The mirth of the tambourines is stilled,the noise of the jubilant
        has ceased,the mirth of the lyre is stilled.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'No more do they drink wine with singing;strong drink is bitter to
        those who drink it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  The wasted city is broken down;  every house is shut up so that
        none can enter.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  There is an outcry in the streets for lack of wine;  all joy has
        grown dark;the gladness of the earth is banished.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Desolation is left in the city;the gates are battered into ruins.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For thus it shall be in the midst of the earthamong the nations, 
        as when an olive tree is beaten,as at the gleaning when the grape harvest
        is done.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'They lift up their voices, they sing for joy;over the majesty of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> they shout from the west.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '24:14 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  Therefore in the east[[COMMENT(0)]] give glory to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;in
        the coastlands of the sea, give glory to the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel.  '
      comments:
      - number: '24:15 '
        content: 'Hebrew , or '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  From the ends of the earth we hear songs of praise,of glory to
        the Righteous One.But I say, \u201CI waste away,I waste away. Woe is me!For
        the traitors have betrayed,with betrayal the traitors have betrayed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  Terror and the pit and the snare[[COMMENT(0)]]are upon you, O inhabitant
        of the earth!  '
      comments:
      - number: '24:17 '
        content: The Hebrew words for , , and sound alike
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  He who flees at the sound of the terrorshall fall into the pit,and
        he who climbs out of the pitshall be caught in the snare.For the windows
        of heaven are opened,and the foundations of the earth tremble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The earth is utterly broken,the earth is split apart,the earth is
        violently shaken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The earth staggers like a drunken man;it sways like a hut;  its transgression
        lies heavy upon it,and it falls, and will not rise again.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'On that day the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will punishthe host of
        heaven, in heaven,and the kings of the earth, on the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  They will be gathered togetheras prisoners in a pit;they will be
        shut up in a prison,and after many days they will be punished.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  Then the moon will be confoundedand the sun ashamed,for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts reignson Mount Zion and in Jerusalem,and his glory will be before
        his elders.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Will Swallow Up Death Forever'
      title: God Will Swallow Up Death Forever
      number: 1
      content: '  O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you are my God;  I will exalt you;
        I will praise your name,for you have done wonderful things,  plans formed
        of old, faithful and sure.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "For you have made the city a heap,the fortified city a ruin;the foreigners\u2019
        palace is a city no more;it will never be rebuilt.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  Therefore strong peoples will glorify you;cities of ruthless nations
        will fear you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  For you have been a stronghold to the poor,a stronghold to the
        needy in his distress,  a shelter from the storm and a shade from the heat; 
        for the breath of the ruthless is like a storm against a wall,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  like heat in a dry place.You subdue the noise of the foreigners;as
        heat by the shade of a cloud,so the song of the ruthless is put down.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  On this mountain the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts will
        make for all peoplesa feast of rich food, a feast of well-aged wine,  of
        rich food full of marrow, of aged wine well refined.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And he will swallow up on this mountainthe covering that is cast
        over all peoples,  the veil that is spread over all nations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  He will swallow up death forever;and the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>
        will wipe away tears from all faces,and the reproach of his people he will
        take away from all the earth,  for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has spoken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "It will be said on that day,\u201CBehold, this is our God; we have
        waited for him, that he might save us.This is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;
        we have waited for him;  let us be glad and rejoice in his salvation.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For the hand of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will rest on this
        mountain,and Moab shall be trampled down in his place,as straw is trampled
        down in a dunghill.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '25:10 '
        content: The Hebrew words for and for the Moabite town (Jeremiah 48:2) sound
          alike
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  And he will spread out his hands in the midst of itas a swimmer
        spreads his hands out to swim,but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  will lay
        low his pompous pride together with the skill[[COMMENT(0)]] of his hands.  '
      comments:
      - number: '25:11 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: And the high fortifications of his walls he will bring down,lay low,
        and cast to the ground, to the dust.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: You Keep Him in Perfect Peace'
      title: You Keep Him in Perfect Peace
      number: 1
      content: "  In that day this song will be sung in the land of Judah:\u201CWe
        have a strong city;he sets up salvationas walls and bulwarks.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  Open the gates,that the righteous nation that keeps faith may enter
        in.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  You keep him in perfect peacewhose mind is stayed on you,because
        he trusts in you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Trust in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> forever,for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> is an everlasting rock.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  For he has humbledthe inhabitants of the height,the lofty city.He
        lays it low, lays it low to the ground,casts it to the dust.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The foot tramples it,the feet of the poor,the steps of the needy.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The path of the righteous is level;  you make level the way of the
        righteous.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'In the path of your judgments,O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, we wait
        for you;  your name and remembranceare the desire of our soul.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'My soul yearns for you in the night;my spirit within me earnestly
        seeks you.  For when your judgments are in the earth,the inhabitants of the
        world learn righteousness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  If favor is shown to the wicked,he does not learn righteousness;in
        the land of uprightness he deals corruptlyand does not see the majesty of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, your hand is lifted up,but they do
        not see it.Let them see your zeal for your people, and be ashamed.Let the
        fire for your adversaries consume them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you will ordain peace for us,for you
        have indeed done for us all our works.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God,  other lords besides you have
        ruled over us,  but your name alone we bring to remembrance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'They are dead, they will not live;they are shades, they will not
        arise;to that end you have visited them with destructionand wiped out all
        remembrance of them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  But you have increased the nation, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,you
        have increased the nation; you are glorified;  you have enlarged all the
        borders of the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, in distress they sought you;they poured
        out a whispered prayerwhen your discipline was upon them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  Like a pregnant womanwho writhes and cries out in her pangswhen
        she is near to giving birth,so were we because of you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  we were pregnant, we writhed,but we have given birth to wind.We
        have accomplished no deliverance in the earth,and the inhabitants of the
        world have not fallen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  Your dead shall live; their bodies shall rise.You who dwell in
        the dust, awake and sing for joy!For your dew is a dew of light,and the earth
        will give birth to the dead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Come, my people, enter your chambers,and shut your doors behind you;hide
        yourselves for a little whileuntil the fury has passed by.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  For behold, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is coming out from
        his placeto punish the inhabitants of the earth for their iniquity,and the
        earth will disclose the blood shed on it,and will no more cover its slain.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Redemption of Israel'
      title: The Redemption of Israel
      number: 1
      content: '  In that day the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> with his hard and great
        and strong sword will punish Leviathan the fleeing serpent, Leviathan the
        twisting serpent, and he will slay the dragon that is in the sea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "In that day,  \u201CA pleasant vineyard,[[COMMENT(0)]]  sing of it!  "
      comments:
      - number: '27:2 '
        content: 'Many Hebrew manuscripts '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, am its keeper;every moment I
        water it.Lest anyone punish it,I keep it night and day;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I have no wrath.  Would that I had thorns and briers to battle!I
        would march against them,I would burn them up together.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Or let them lay hold of my protection,let them make peace with me,let
        them make peace with me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  In days to come[[COMMENT(0)]] Jacob shall take root,Israel shall
        blossom and put forth shootsand fill the whole world with fruit.  '
      comments:
      - number: '27:6 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  Has he struck them as he struck those who struck them?Or have they
        been slain as their slayers were slain?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  Measure by measure,[[COMMENT(0)]] by exile you contended with them; 
        he removed them with his fierce breath in the day of the east wind.  '
      comments:
      - number: '27:8 '
        content: 'Or ; the meaning of the Hebrew word is uncertainOr '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Therefore by this the guilt of Jacob will be atoned for,and this
        will be the full fruit of the removal of his sin:[[COMMENT(0)]]  when he
        makes all the stones of the altarslike chalkstones crushed to pieces,no Asherim
        or incense altars will remain standing.  '
      comments:
      - number: '27:9 '
        content: 'Septuagint '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  For the fortified city is solitary,a habitation deserted and forsaken,
        like the wilderness;there the calf grazes;there it lies down and strips its
        branches.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When its boughs are dry, they are broken;women come and make a fire
        of them.  For this is a people without discernment;therefore he who made
        them will not have compassion on them;he who formed them will show them no
        favor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'In that day from the river Euphrates[[COMMENT(0)]] to the Brook of
        Egypt the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will thresh out the grain, and you
        will be gleaned one by one, O people of Israel. '
      comments:
      - number: '27:12 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: And in that day a great trumpet will be blown, and those who were
        lost in the land of Assyria and those who were driven out to the land of
        Egypt will come and worship the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> on the holy mountain
        at Jerusalem.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment on Ephraim and Jerusalem'
      title: Judgment on Ephraim and Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: '  Ah, the proud crown of the drunkards of Ephraim,and the fading
        flower of its glorious beauty,which is on the head of the rich valley of
        those overcome with wine!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Behold, the Lord has one who is mighty and strong;like a storm of
        hail, a destroying tempest,like a storm of mighty, overflowing waters,he
        casts down to the earth with his hand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  The proud crown of the drunkards of Ephraimwill be trodden underfoot;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  and the fading flower of its glorious beauty,which is on the head
        of the rich valley,will be like a first-ripe fig[[COMMENT(0)]] before the
        summer:when someone sees it, he swallows itas soon as it is in his hand.  '
      comments:
      - number: '28:4 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  In that day the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts will be a
        crown of glory,[[COMMENT(0)]]and a diadem of beauty, to the remnant of his
        people,  '
      comments:
      - number: '28:5 '
        content: The Hebrew words for and sound alike
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and a spirit of justice to him who sits in judgment,and strength
        to those who turn back the battle at the gate.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  These also reel with wineand stagger with strong drink;the priest
        and the prophet reel with strong drink,they are swallowed by[[COMMENT(0)]]
        wine,they stagger with strong drink,they reel in vision,they stumble in giving
        judgment.  '
      comments:
      - number: '28:7 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For all tables are full of filthy vomit,with no space left.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "  \u201CTo whom will he teach knowledge,and to whom will he explain
        the message?Those who are weaned from the milk,those taken from the breast?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For it is precept upon precept, precept upon precept,line upon line,
        line upon line,here a little, there a little.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  For by people of strange lipsand with a foreign tonguethe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will speak to this people,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "to whom he has said,  \u201CThis is rest;give rest to the weary;and
        this is repose\u201D;yet they would not hear.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: A Cornerstone in Zion'
      title: A Cornerstone in Zion
      number: 13
      content: 'And the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be to themprecept
        upon precept, precept upon precept,line upon line, line upon line,here a
        little, there a little,  that they may go, and fall backward,and be broken,
        and snared, and taken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore hear the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you scoffers,who
        rule this people in Jerusalem!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Because you have said, \u201CWe have made a covenant with death,and
        with Sheol we have an agreement,when the overwhelming whip passes throughit
        will not come to us,for we have made lies our refuge,and in falsehood we
        have taken shelter\u201D;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "therefore thus says the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>,  \u201CBehold,
        I am the one who has laid[[COMMENT(0)]] as a foundation in Zion,a stone,
        a tested stone,a precious cornerstone, of a sure foundation:\u2018Whoever
        believes will not be in haste.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '28:16 '
        content: 'Dead Sea Scroll '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And I will make justice the line,and righteousness the plumb line;and
        hail will sweep away the refuge of lies,and waters will overwhelm the shelter.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then your covenant with death will be annulled,and your agreement
        with Sheol will not stand;when the overwhelming scourge passes through,you
        will be beaten down by it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'As often as it passes through it will take you;  for morning by morning
        it will pass through,by day and by night;and it will be sheer terror to understand
        the message.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For the bed is too short to stretch oneself on,and the covering too
        narrow to wrap oneself in.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will rise up as on Mount Perazim; 
        as in the Valley of Gibeon he will be roused;to do his deed\u2014strange
        is his deed!and to work his work\u2014alien is his work!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Now therefore do not scoff,lest your bonds be made strong;for I have
        heard a decree of destructionfrom the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> of
        hosts against the whole land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Give ear, and hear my voice;give attention, and hear my speech.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Does he who plows for sowing plow continually?Does he continually
        open and harrow his ground?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  When he has leveled its surface,does he not scatter dill, sow cumin,and
        put in wheat in rowsand barley in its proper place,and emmer[[COMMENT(0)]]
        as the border?  '
      comments:
      - number: '28:25 '
        content: A type of wheat
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '  For he is rightly instructed;his God teaches him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Dill is not threshed with a threshing sledge,nor is a cart wheel
        rolled over cumin,but dill is beaten out with a stick,and cumin with a rod.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Does one crush grain for bread?No, he does not thresh it forever;[[COMMENT(0)]]when
        he drives his cart wheel over itwith his horses, he does not crush it.  '
      comments:
      - number: '28:28 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: This also comes from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts;he is
        wonderful in counseland excellent in wisdom.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Siege of Jerusalem'
      title: The Siege of Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: '  Ah, Ariel, Ariel,the city where David encamped!Add year to year;let
        the feasts run their round.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Yet I will distress Ariel,and there shall be moaning and lamentation,and
        she shall be to me like an Ariel.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '29:2 '
        content: "could mean , or (2 Samuel 23:20), or (Ezekiel 43:15\u201316)"
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  And I will encamp against you all around,and will besiege you with
        towersand I will raise siegeworks against you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  And you will be brought low; from the earth you shall speak,and
        from the dust your speech will be bowed down;your voice shall come from the
        ground like the voice of a ghost,and from the dust your speech shall whisper.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But the multitude of your foreign foes shall be like small dust,and
        the multitude of the ruthless like passing chaff.  And in an instant, suddenly,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  you will be visited by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hostswith
        thunder and with earthquake and great noise,with whirlwind and tempest, and
        the flame of a devouring fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the multitude of all the nations that fight against Ariel,all
        that fight against her and her stronghold and distress her,shall be like
        a dream, a vision of the night.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  As when a hungry man dreams, and behold, he is eating,and awakes
        with his hunger not satisfied,or as when a thirsty man dreams, and behold,
        he is drinking,and awakes faint, with his thirst not quenched,so shall the
        multitude of all the nations bethat fight against Mount Zion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Astonish yourselves[[COMMENT(0)]] and be astonished;blind yourselves
        and be blind!Be drunk, but not with wine;  stagger, but not with strong drink!  '
      comments:
      - number: '29:9 '
        content: 'Or Or Or '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has poured out upon youa spirit
        of deep sleep,and has closed your eyes (the prophets),and covered your heads
        (the seers).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the vision of all this has become to you like the words of a
        book that is sealed. When men give it to one who can read, saying, \u201CRead
        this,\u201D he says, \u201CI cannot, for it is sealed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And when they give the book to one who cannot read, saying, \u201CRead
        this,\u201D he says, \u201CI cannot read.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the Lord said:\u201CBecause this people draw near with their
        mouthand honor me with their lips,while their hearts are far from me,and
        their fear of me is a commandment taught by men,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "therefore, behold, I will againdo wonderful things with this people,with
        wonder upon wonder;and the wisdom of their wise men shall perish,and the
        discernment of their discerning men shall be hidden.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Ah, you who hide deep from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your counsel,whose
        deeds are in the dark,and who say, \u201CWho sees us? Who knows us?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  You turn things upside down!Shall the potter be regarded as the
        clay,that the thing made should say of its maker,\u201CHe did not make me\u201D;or
        the thing formed say of him who formed it,\u201CHe has no understanding\u201D?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Is it not yet a very little while  until Lebanon shall be turned
        into a fruitful field,and the fruitful field shall be regarded as a forest?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'In that day the deaf shall hear  the words of a book,and out of their
        gloom and darkness  the eyes of the blind shall see.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  The meek shall obtain fresh joy in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and
        the poor among mankind shall exult in the Holy One of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For the ruthless shall come to nothingand the scoffer cease,and all
        who watch to do evil shall be cut off,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'who by a word make a man out to be an offender,and lay a snare for
        him who reproves in the gate,and with an empty plea turn aside him who is
        in the right.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Therefore thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, who redeemed
        Abraham, concerning the house of Jacob:\u201CJacob shall no more be ashamed,no
        more shall his face grow pale.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For when he sees his children,  the work of my hands, in his midst,they
        will sanctify my name;  they will sanctify the Holy One of Jacoband will
        stand in awe of the God of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And those who go astray in spirit will come to understanding,and
        those who murmur will accept instruction.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Do Not Go Down to Egypt'
      title: Do Not Go Down to Egypt
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CAh, stubborn children,\u201D declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, 
        \u201Cwho carry out a plan, but not mine,and who make an alliance,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        but not of my Spirit,that they may add sin to sin;  "
      comments:
      - number: '30:1 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  who set out to go down to Egypt,without asking for my direction,to
        take refuge in the protection of Pharaohand to seek shelter in the shadow
        of Egypt!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  Therefore shall the protection of Pharaoh turn to your shame,and
        the shelter in the shadow of Egypt to your humiliation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For though his officials are at Zoanand his envoys reach Hanes,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "everyone comes to shamethrough a people that cannot profit them,that
        brings neither help nor profit,but shame and disgrace.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'An oracle on the beasts of the Negeb.Through a land of trouble and
        anguish,from where come the lioness and the lion,the adder and the flying
        fiery serpent,they carry their riches on the backs of donkeys,and their treasures
        on the humps of camels,to a people that cannot profit them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: A Rebellious People'
      title: A Rebellious People
      number: 7
      content: "Egypt\u2019s help is worthless and empty;therefore I have called
        her  \u201CRahab who sits still.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And now, go, write it before them on a tabletand inscribe it in a
        book,that it may be for the time to comeas a witness forever.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '30:8 '
        content: 'Some Hebrew manuscripts, Syriac, Targum, Vulgate, and Greek versions;
          Masoretic Text '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  For they are a rebellious people,lying children,children unwilling
        to hearthe instruction of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "  who say to the seers, \u201CDo not see,\u201Dand to the prophets,
        \u201CDo not prophesy to us what is right;speak to us smooth things,prophesy
        illusions,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "leave the way, turn aside from the path,let us hear no more about
        the Holy One of Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Therefore thus says the Holy One of Israel,\u201CBecause you despise
        this wordand trust in oppression and perversenessand rely on them,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'therefore this iniquity shall be to you  like a breach in a high
        wall, bulging out and about to collapse,whose breaking comes suddenly, in
        an instant;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "and its breaking is like that of a potter\u2019s vesselthat is smashed
        so ruthlesslythat among its fragments not a shard is foundwith which to take
        fire from the hearth,or to dip up water out of the cistern.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For thus said the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>, the Holy One of
        Israel,\u201CIn returning[[COMMENT(0)]] and rest you shall be saved;in quietness
        and in trust shall be your strength.\u201DBut you were unwilling, "
      comments:
      - number: '30:15 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "and you said,\u201CNo! We will flee upon horses\u201D;therefore you
        shall flee away;and, \u201CWe will ride upon swift steeds\u201D;therefore
        your pursuers shall be swift.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: The  Will Be Gracious'
      title: The  Will Be Gracious
      number: 17
      content: '  A thousand shall flee at the threat of one;at the threat of five
        you shall flee,till you are leftlike a flagstaff on the top of a mountain,like
        a signal on a hill.<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Therefore the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  waits to be gracious to
        you,and therefore he exalts himself to show mercy to you.For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is a God of justice;  blessed are all those who wait for him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For a people shall dwell in Zion, in Jerusalem; you shall weep no
        more. He will surely be gracious to you at the sound of your cry. As soon
        as he hears it, he answers you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And though the Lord give you the bread of adversity and the water
        of affliction, yet your Teacher will not hide himself anymore, but your eyes
        shall see your Teacher. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And your ears shall hear a word behind you, saying, \u201CThis is
        the way, walk in it,\u201D when you turn to the right or when you turn to
        the left. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then you will defile your carved idols overlaid with silver and your
        gold-plated metal images. You will scatter them as unclean things. You will
        say to them, \u201CBe gone!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  And he will give rain for the seed with which you sow the ground,
        and bread, the produce of the ground, which will be rich and plenteous. In
        that day your livestock will graze in large pastures, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'and the oxen and the donkeys that work the ground will eat seasoned
        fodder, which has been winnowed with shovel and fork. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And on every lofty mountain and every high hill there will be brooks
        running with water, in the day of the great slaughter, when the towers fall. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Moreover, the light of the moon will be as the light of the sun,
        and the light of the sun will be sevenfold, as the light of seven days, in
        the day when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> binds up the brokenness of his
        people, and heals the wounds inflicted by his blow.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Behold, the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> comes from afar,burning
        with his anger, and in thick rising smoke;[[COMMENT(0)]]his lips are full
        of fury,and his tongue is like a devouring fire;  '
      comments:
      - number: '30:27 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '  his breath is like an overflowing streamthat reaches up to the
        neck;to sift the nations with the sieve of destruction,and to place on the
        jaws of the peoples a bridle that leads astray.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'You shall have a song as in the night when a holy feast is kept,
        and gladness of heart, as when one sets out to the sound of the flute to
        go to the mountain of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, to the Rock of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  will cause his majestic voice
        to be heard and the descending blow of his arm to be seen, in furious anger
        and a flame of devouring fire, with a cloudburst and storm and hailstones. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The Assyrians will be terror-stricken at the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        when he strikes with his rod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And every stroke of the appointed staff that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        lays on them will be to the sound of tambourines and lyres. Battling with
        brandished arm, he will fight with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: For a burning place[[COMMENT(0)]] has long been prepared; indeed,
        for the king it is made ready, its pyre made deep and wide, with fire and
        wood in abundance; the breath of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, like a
        stream of sulfur, kindles it.
      comments:
      - number: '30:33 '
        content: 'Or '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Woe to Those Who Go Down to Egypt'
      title: Woe to Those Who Go Down to Egypt
      number: 1
      content: '  Woe[[COMMENT(0)]] to those who go down to Egypt for helpand rely
        on horses,who trust in chariots because they are manyand in horsemen because
        they are very strong,but do not look to the Holy One of Israelor consult
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!  '
      comments:
      - number: '31:1 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And yet he is wise and brings disaster;  he does not call back his
        words,but will arise against the house of the evildoersand against the helpers
        of those who work iniquity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The Egyptians are man, and not God,and their horses are flesh, and
        not spirit.When the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> stretches out his hand,the
        helper will stumble, and he who is helped will fall,and they will all perish
        together.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For thus the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me,  \u201CAs a
        lion or a young lion growls over his prey,and when a band of shepherds is
        called out against himhe is not terrified by their shoutingor daunted at
        their noise,  so the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts will come downto
        fight[[COMMENT(0)]] on Mount Zion and on its hill.  "
      comments:
      - number: '31:4 '
        content: The Hebrew words for and sound alike
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "  Like birds hovering, so the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hostswill
        protect Jerusalem;he will protect and deliver it;he will spare and rescue
        it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  Turn to him from whom people[[COMMENT(0)]] have deeply revolted,
        O children of Israel. '
      comments:
      - number: '31:6 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For in that day everyone shall cast away his idols of silver and
        his idols of gold, which your hands have sinfully made for you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "  \u201CAnd the Assyrian shall fall by a sword, not of man;and a
        sword, not of man, shall devour him;and he shall flee from the sword,and
        his young men shall be put to forced labor.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "  His rock shall pass away in terror,and his officers desert the
        standard in panic,\u201Ddeclares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, whose fire
        is in Zion,and whose furnace is in Jerusalem."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A King Will Reign in Righteousness'
      title: A King Will Reign in Righteousness
      number: 1
      content: '  Behold, a king will reign in righteousness,and princes will rule
        in justice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  Each will be like a hiding place from the wind,a shelter from the
        storm,  like streams of water in a dry place,like the shade of a great rock
        in a weary land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  Then the eyes of those who see will not be closed,and the ears
        of those who hear will give attention.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The heart of the hasty will understand and know,  and the tongue
        of the stammerers will hasten to speak distinctly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  The fool will no more be called noble,nor the scoundrel said to
        be honorable.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For the fool speaks folly,and his heart is busy with iniquity,to
        practice ungodliness,to utter error concerning the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, 
        to leave the craving of the hungry unsatisfied,and to deprive the thirsty
        of drink.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "As for the scoundrel\u2014his devices are evil;he plans wicked schemesto
        ruin the poor with lying words,even when the plea of the needy is right.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Complacent Women Warned of Disaster'
      title: Complacent Women Warned of Disaster
      number: 8
      content: 'But he who is noble plans noble things,and on noble things he stands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  Rise up, you women who are at ease, hear my voice;you complacent
        daughters, give ear to my speech.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'In little more than a yearyou will shudder, you complacent women;for
        the grape harvest fails,the fruit harvest will not come.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Tremble, you women who are at ease,shudder, you complacent ones; 
        strip, and make yourselves bare,  and tie sackcloth around your waist.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  Beat your breasts for the pleasant fields,for the fruitful vine,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  for the soil of my peoplegrowing up in thorns and briers,  yes,
        for all the joyous housesin the exultant city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For the palace is forsaken,the populous city deserted;the hill and
        the watchtowerwill become dens forever,  a joy of wild donkeys,a pasture
        of flocks;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'until the Spirit is poured upon us from on high,and the wilderness
        becomes a fruitful field,and the fruitful field is deemed a forest.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then justice will dwell in the wilderness,and righteousness abide
        in the fruitful field.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  And the effect of righteousness will be peace,and the result of
        righteousness, quietness and trust[[COMMENT(0)]] forever.  '
      comments:
      - number: '32:17 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'My people will abide in a peaceful habitation,in secure dwellings,
        and in quiet resting places.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  And it will hail when the forest falls down,  and the city will
        be utterly laid low.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  Happy are you who sow beside all waters,who let the feet of the
        ox and the donkey range free.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: O , Be Gracious to Us'
      title: O , Be Gracious to Us
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>    Ah, you destroyer,who yourself have
        not been destroyed,you traitor,whom none has betrayed!When you have ceased
        to destroy,you will be destroyed;and when you have finished betraying,they
        will betray you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, be gracious to us; we wait for you.Be
        our arm every morning,our salvation in the time of trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  At the tumultuous noise peoples flee;when you lift yourself up,
        nations are scattered,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and your spoil is gathered as the caterpillar gathers;  as locusts
        leap, it is leapt upon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is exalted, for he dwells on high;he
        will fill Zion with justice and righteousness,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "  and he will be the stability of your times,abundance of salvation,
        wisdom, and knowledge;the fear of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is Zion\u2019s[[COMMENT(0)]]
        treasure.  "
      comments:
      - number: '33:6 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Behold, their heroes cry in the streets;  the envoys of peace weep
        bitterly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  The highways lie waste;the traveler ceases.  Covenants are broken;cities[[COMMENT(0)]]
        are despised;there is no regard for man.  '
      comments:
      - number: '33:8 '
        content: 'Masoretic Text; Dead Sea Scroll '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  The land mourns and languishes;Lebanon is confounded and withers
        away;Sharon is like a desert,and Bashan and Carmel shake off their leaves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "  \u201CNow I will arise,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201Cnow
        I will lift myself up;now I will be exalted.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  You conceive chaff; you give birth to stubble;your breath is a
        fire that will consume you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And the peoples will be as if burned to lime,  like thorns cut down,
        that are burned in the fire.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Hear, you who are far off, what I have done;and you who are near,
        acknowledge my might.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The sinners in Zion are afraid;trembling has seized the godless: 
        \u201CWho among us can dwell with the consuming fire?Who among us can dwell
        with everlasting burnings?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  He who walks righteously and speaks uprightly,who despises the
        gain of oppressions,who shakes his hands, lest they hold a bribe,who stops
        his ears from hearing of bloodshed  and shuts his eyes from looking on evil,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'he will dwell on the heights;his place of defense will be the fortresses
        of rocks;  his bread will be given him; his water will be sure.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  Your eyes will behold the king in his beauty;  they will see a
        land that stretches afar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "  Your heart will muse on the terror:\u201CWhere is he who counted,
        where is he who weighed the tribute?Where is he who counted the towers?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  You will see no more the insolent people,the people of an obscure
        speech that you cannot comprehend,stammering in a tongue that you cannot
        understand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Behold Zion, the city of our appointed feasts!  Your eyes will see
        Jerusalem,an untroubled habitation, an immovable tent,whose stakes will never
        be plucked up,nor will any of its cords be broken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But there the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> in majesty will be for
        usa place of broad rivers and streams,  where no galley with oars can go,nor
        majestic ship can pass.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is our judge; the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is our lawgiver;the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is our king; he will save
        us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Your cords hang loose;they cannot hold the mast firm in its placeor
        keep the sail spread out.  Then prey and spoil in abundance will be divided;even
        the lame will take the prey.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And no inhabitant will say, \u201CI am sick\u201D;  the people who
        dwell there will be forgiven their iniquity."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment on the Nations'
      title: Judgment on the Nations
      number: 1
      content: '  Draw near, O nations, to hear,and give attention, O peoples!Let
        the earth hear, and all that fills it;the world, and all that comes from
        it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is enraged against all the nations,and
        furious against all their host;he has devoted them to destruction,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        has given them over for slaughter.  '
      comments:
      - number: '34:2 '
        content: That is, set apart (devoted) as an offering to the Lord (for destruction);
          also verse 5
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Their slain shall be cast out,and the stench of their corpses shall
        rise;  the mountains shall flow with their blood.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  All the host of heaven shall rot away,and the skies roll up like
        a scroll.All their host shall fall,as leaves fall from the vine,like leaves
        falling from the fig tree.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For my sword has drunk its fill in the heavens;behold, it descends
        for judgment upon Edom,upon the people I have devoted to destruction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has a sword; it is sated with blood;it
        is gorged with fat,with the blood of lambs and goats,with the fat of the
        kidneys of rams.  For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has a sacrifice in
        Bozrah,a great slaughter in the land of Edom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  Wild oxen shall fall with them,and young steers with the mighty
        bulls.Their land shall drink its fill of blood,and their soil shall be gorged
        with fat.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has a day of vengeance,a year
        of recompense for the cause of Zion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  And the streams of Edom[[COMMENT(0)]] shall be turned into pitch,and
        her soil into sulfur;her land shall become burning pitch.  '
      comments:
      - number: '34:9 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Night and day it shall not be quenched;  its smoke shall go up forever. 
        From generation to generation it shall lie waste;none shall pass through
        it forever and ever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  But the hawk and the porcupine[[COMMENT(0)]] shall possess it,the
        owl and the raven shall dwell in it.  He shall stretch the line of confusion
        over it,and the plumb line of emptiness.  '
      comments:
      - number: '34:11 '
        content: 'The identity of the animals rendered and is uncertainHebrew '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Its nobles\u2014there is no one there to call it a kingdom,and all
        its princes shall be nothing.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  Thorns shall grow over its strongholds,nettles and thistles in
        its fortresses.It shall be the haunt of jackals,an abode for ostriches.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '34:13 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  And wild animals shall meet with hyenas;the wild goat shall cry
        to his fellow;indeed, there the night bird[[COMMENT(0)]] settlesand finds
        for herself a resting place.  '
      comments:
      - number: '34:14 '
        content: Identity uncertain
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'There the owl nests and laysand hatches and gathers her young in
        her shadow;indeed, there the hawks are gathered,each one with her mate.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Seek and read from the book of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:Not
        one of these shall be missing;none shall be without her mate.For the mouth
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has commanded,and his Spirit has gathered
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  He has cast the lot for them;his hand has portioned it out to them
        with the line;they shall possess it forever;from generation to generation
        they shall dwell in it.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Ransomed Shall Return'
      title: The Ransomed Shall Return
      number: 1
      content: '    The wilderness and the dry land shall be glad;  the desert shall
        rejoice and blossom like the crocus;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'it shall blossom abundantlyand rejoice with joy and singing.  The
        glory of Lebanon shall be given to it,the majesty of Carmel and Sharon. 
        They shall see the glory of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,the majesty of
        our God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  Strengthen the weak hands,and make firm the feeble knees.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Say to those who have an anxious heart,\u201CBe strong; fear not! 
        Behold, your Godwill come with vengeance,with the recompense of God.He will
        come and save you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  Then the eyes of the blind shall be opened,and the ears of the
        deaf unstopped;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  then shall the lame man leap like a deer,and the tongue of the
        mute sing for joy.  For waters break forth in the wilderness,and streams
        in the desert;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  the burning sand shall become a pool,and the thirsty ground springs
        of water;in the haunt of jackals, where they lie down,the grass shall become
        reeds and rushes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  And a highway shall be there,and it shall be called the Way of
        Holiness;  the unclean shall not pass over it.It shall belong to those who
        walk on the way;even if they are fools, they shall not go astray.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '35:8 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'No lion shall be there,nor shall any ravenous beast come up on it;they
        shall not be found there,but the redeemed shall walk there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  And the ransomed of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> shall returnand
        come to Zion with singing;  everlasting joy shall be upon their heads;they
        shall obtain gladness and joy,and sorrow and sighing shall flee away.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Sennacherib Invades Judah'
      title: Sennacherib Invades Judah
      number: 1
      content: '    In the fourteenth year of King Hezekiah, Sennacherib king of
        Assyria came up against all the fortified cities of Judah and took them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the king of Assyria sent the Rabshakeh[[COMMENT(0)]] from Lachish
        to King Hezekiah at Jerusalem, with a great army. And he stood by the conduit
        of the upper pool on the highway to the Washer\u2019s Field. "
      comments:
      - number: '36:2 '
        content: is the title of a high-ranking Assyrian military officer
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And there came out to him Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, who was over
        the household, and Shebna the secretary, and Joah the son of Asaph, the recorder.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And the Rabshakeh said to them, \u201CSay to Hezekiah, \u2018Thus
        says the great king, the king of Assyria: On what do you rest this trust
        of yours? "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Do you think that mere words are strategy and power for war? In whom
        do you now trust, that you have rebelled against me? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Behold, you are trusting in Egypt, that broken reed of a staff, which
        will pierce the hand of any man who leans on it. Such is Pharaoh king of
        Egypt to all who trust in him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But if you say to me, \u201CWe trust in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God,\u201D is it not he whose high places and altars Hezekiah has removed,
        saying to Judah and to Jerusalem, \u201CYou shall worship before this altar\u201D? "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Come now, make a wager with my master the king of Assyria: I will
        give you two thousand horses, if you are able on your part to set riders
        on them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "How then can you repulse a single captain among the least of my master\u2019s
        servants, when you trust in Egypt for chariots and for horsemen? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Moreover, is it without the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that I have
        come up against this land to destroy it? The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        said to me, \u201CGo up against this land and destroy it.\u201D\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Eliakim, Shebna, and Joah said to the Rabshakeh, \u201CPlease
        speak to your servants in Aramaic, for we understand it. Do not speak to
        us in the language of Judah within the hearing of the people who are on the
        wall.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But the Rabshakeh said, \u201CHas my master sent me to speak these
        words to your master and to you, and not to the men sitting on the wall,
        who are doomed with you to eat their own dung and drink their own urine?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then the Rabshakeh stood and called out in a loud voice in the language
        of Judah: \u201CHear the words of the great king, the king of Assyria! "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Thus says the king: \u2018Do not let Hezekiah deceive you, for he
        will not be able to deliver you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Do not let Hezekiah make you trust in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        by saying, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will surely deliver us.
        This city will not be given into the hand of the king of Assyria.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Do not listen to Hezekiah. For thus says the king of Assyria: Make
        your peace with me[[COMMENT(0)]] and come out to me. Then each one of you
        will eat of his own vine, and each one of his own fig tree, and each one
        of you will drink the water of his own cistern, '
      comments:
      - number: '36:16 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'until I come and take you away to a land like your own land, a land
        of grain and wine, a land of bread and vineyards. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Beware lest Hezekiah mislead you by saying, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will deliver us.\u201D Has any of the gods of the nations delivered his land
        out of the hand of the king of Assyria? "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Where are the gods of Hamath and Arpad? Where are the gods of Sepharvaim?
        Have they delivered Samaria out of my hand? '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Who among all the gods of these lands have delivered their lands
        out of my hand, that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> should deliver Jerusalem
        out of my hand?\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But they were silent and answered him not a word, for the king\u2019s
        command was, \u201CDo not answer him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Then Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, who was over the household, and Shebna
        the secretary, and Joah the son of Asaph, the recorder, came to Hezekiah
        with their clothes torn, and told him the words of the Rabshakeh.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Hezekiah Seeks Isaiah\u2019s Help"
      title: "Hezekiah Seeks Isaiah\u2019s Help"
      number: 1
      content: '    As soon as King Hezekiah heard it, he tore his clothes and covered
        himself with sackcloth and went into the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he sent Eliakim, who was over the household, and Shebna the secretary,
        and the senior priests, covered with sackcloth, to the prophet Isaiah the
        son of Amoz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "They said to him, \u201CThus says Hezekiah, \u2018This day is a day
        of distress, of rebuke, and of disgrace; children have come to the point
        of birth, and there is no strength to bring them forth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "It may be that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will hear
        the words of the Rabshakeh, whom his master the king of Assyria has sent
        to mock the living God, and will rebuke the words that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God has heard; therefore lift up your prayer for the remnant that is
        left.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When the servants of King Hezekiah came to Isaiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Isaiah said to them, \u201CSay to your master, \u2018Thus says the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: Do not be afraid because of the words that you
        have heard, with which the young men of the king of Assyria have reviled
        me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Behold, I will put a spirit in him, so that he shall hear a rumor
        and return to his own land, and I will make him fall by the sword in his
        own land.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The Rabshakeh returned, and found the king of Assyria fighting against
        Libnah, for he had heard that the king had left Lachish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Now the king heard concerning Tirhakah king of Cush,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        \u201CHe has set out to fight against you.\u201D And when he heard it, he
        sent messengers to Hezekiah, saying, "
      comments:
      - number: '37:9 '
        content: 'Probably '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThus shall you speak to Hezekiah king of Judah: \u2018Do not
        let your God in whom you trust deceive you by promising that Jerusalem will
        not be given into the hand of the king of Assyria. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Behold, you have heard what the kings of Assyria have done to all
        lands, devoting them to destruction. And shall you be delivered? '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Have the gods of the nations delivered them, the nations that my
        fathers destroyed, Gozan, Haran, Rezeph, and the people of Eden who were
        in Telassar? '
      comments: []
    - name: "13: Hezekiah\u2019s Prayer for Deliverance"
      title: "Hezekiah\u2019s Prayer for Deliverance"
      number: 13
      content: "Where is the king of Hamath, the king of Arpad, the king of the city
        of Sepharvaim, the king of Hena, or the king of Ivvah?\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Hezekiah received the letter from the hand of the messengers, and
        read it; and Hezekiah went up to the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and spread it before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Hezekiah prayed to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, God of Israel, enthroned
        above the cherubim, you are the God, you alone, of all the kingdoms of the
        earth; you have made heaven and earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Incline your ear, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and hear; open your
        eyes, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and see; and hear all the words of Sennacherib,
        which he has sent to mock the living God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Truly, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the kings of Assyria have laid
        waste all the nations and their lands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "and have cast their gods into the fire. For they were no gods, but
        the work of men\u2019s hands, wood and stone. Therefore they were destroyed. "
      comments: []
    - name: "20: Sennacherib\u2019s Fall"
      title: "Sennacherib\u2019s Fall"
      number: 20
      content: "So now, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God, save us from his hand,
        that all the kingdoms of the earth may know that you alone are the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Isaiah the son of Amoz sent to Hezekiah, saying, \u201CThus
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel: Because you have
        prayed to me concerning Sennacherib king of Assyria, "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "this is the word that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has spoken
        concerning him:\u201C\u2018She despises you, she scorns you\u2014  the virgin
        daughter of Zion;she wags her head behind you\u2014the daughter of Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201C\u2018Whom have you mocked and reviled?Against whom have you
        raised your voiceand lifted your eyes to the heights?Against the Holy One
        of Israel!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'By your servants you have mocked the Lord,and you have said, With
        my many chariotsI have gone up the heights of the mountains,to the far recesses
        of Lebanon,  to cut down its tallest cedars,its choicest cypresses,to come
        to its remotest height,its most fruitful forest.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'I dug wellsand drank waters,to dry up with the sole of my footall
        the streams of Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "  \u201C\u2018Have you not heardthat I determined it long ago?I planned
        from days of oldwhat now I bring to pass,that you should make fortified citiescrash
        into heaps of ruins,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'while their inhabitants, shorn of strength,are dismayed and confounded,and
        have become like plants of the fieldand like tender grass,like grass on the
        housetops,blighted[[COMMENT(0)]] before it is grown.  '
      comments:
      - number: '37:27 '
        content: 'Some Hebrew manuscripts and 2 Kings 19:26; most Hebrew manuscripts '
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201C\u2018I know your sitting downand your going out and coming
        in,and your raging against me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "  Because you have raged against meand your complacency has come
        to my ears,I will put my hook in your noseand my bit in your mouth,and I
        will turn you back on the wayby which you came.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CAnd this shall be the sign for you: this year you shall eat
        what grows of itself, and in the second year what springs from that. Then
        in the third year sow and reap, and plant vineyards, and eat their fruit. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And the surviving remnant of the house of Judah shall again take
        root downward and bear fruit upward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'For out of Jerusalem shall go a remnant, and out of Mount Zion a
        band of survivors. The zeal of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts will
        do this.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CTherefore thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> concerning
        the king of Assyria: He shall not come into this city or shoot an arrow there
        or come before it with a shield or cast up a siege mound against it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'By the way that he came, by the same he shall return, and he shall
        not come into this city, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "For I will defend this city to save it, for my own sake and for the
        sake of my servant David.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: '  And the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> went out and struck
        down 185,000 in the camp of the Assyrians. And when people arose early in
        the morning, behold, these were all dead bodies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Then Sennacherib king of Assyria departed and returned home and lived
        at Nineveh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: And as he was worshiping in the house of Nisroch his god, Adrammelech
        and Sharezer, his sons, struck him down with the sword. And after they escaped
        into the land of Ararat, Esarhaddon his son reigned in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Hezekiah\u2019s Sickness and Recovery"
      title: "Hezekiah\u2019s Sickness and Recovery"
      number: 1
      content: "    In those days Hezekiah became sick and was at the point of death.
        And Isaiah the prophet the son of Amoz came to him, and said to him, \u201CThus
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: Set your house in order, for you shall
        die, you shall not recover.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '38:1 '
        content: Or ; also verses 9, 21
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Hezekiah turned his face to the wall and prayed to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and said, \u201CPlease, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, remember how
        I have walked before you in faithfulness and with a whole heart, and have
        done what is good in your sight.\u201D And Hezekiah wept bitterly.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to Isaiah: '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CGo and say to Hezekiah, Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of David your father: I have heard your prayer; I have seen your
        tears. Behold, I will add fifteen years to your life.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '38:5 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I will deliver you and this city out of the hand of the king of Assyria,
        and will defend this city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CThis shall be the sign to you from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will do this thing that he has promised: "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Behold, I will make the shadow cast by the declining sun on the dial
        of Ahaz turn back ten steps.\u201D So the sun turned back on the dial the
        ten steps by which it had declined.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '38:8 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew verse is uncertain
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'A writing of Hezekiah king of Judah, after he had been sick and had
        recovered from his sickness:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I said, In the middle[[COMMENT(0)]] of my daysI must depart;I am
        consigned to the gates of Sheolfor the rest of my years.  '
      comments:
      - number: '38:10 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'I said, I shall not see the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        in the land of the living;I shall look on man no moreamong the inhabitants
        of the world.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "My dwelling is plucked up and removed from me  like a shepherd\u2019s
        tent;  like a weaver I have rolled up my life;  he cuts me off from the loom; 
        from day to night you bring me to an end;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  I calmed myself[[COMMENT(0)]] until morning;like a lion he breaks
        all my bones;from day to night you bring me to an end.  '
      comments:
      - number: '38:13 '
        content: 'Or (with Targum) '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Like a swallow or a crane I chirp;  I moan like a dove.  My eyes
        are weary with looking upward.O Lord, I am oppressed; be my pledge of safety!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'What shall I say? For he has spoken to me,and he himself has done
        it.  I walk slowly all my yearsbecause of the bitterness of my soul.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  O Lord, by these things men live,and in all these is the life of
        my spirit.Oh restore me to health and make me live!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  Behold, it was for my welfarethat I had great bitterness;  but
        in love you have delivered my lifefrom the pit of destruction,  for you have
        cast all my sinsbehind your back.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  For Sheol does not thank you;death does not praise you;those who
        go down to the pit do not hopefor your faithfulness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The living, the living, he thanks you,as I do this day;  the father
        makes known to the childrenyour faithfulness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will save me,and we will play my
        music on stringed instrumentsall the days of our lives,  at the house of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "  Now Isaiah had said, \u201CLet them take a cake of figs and apply
        it to the boil, that he may recover.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Hezekiah also had said, \u201CWhat is the sign that I shall go up
        to the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Envoys from Babylon'
      title: Envoys from Babylon
      number: 1
      content: '    At that time Merodach-baladan the son of Baladan, king of Babylon,
        sent envoys with letters and a present to Hezekiah, for he heard that he
        had been sick and had recovered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Hezekiah welcomed them gladly. And he showed them his treasure
        house, the silver, the gold, the spices, the precious oil, his whole armory,
        all that was found in his storehouses. There was nothing in his house or
        in all his realm that Hezekiah did not show them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Isaiah the prophet came to King Hezekiah, and said to him, \u201CWhat
        did these men say? And from where did they come to you?\u201D Hezekiah said,
        \u201CThey have come to me from a far country, from Babylon.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "He said, \u201CWhat have they seen in your house?\u201D Hezekiah
        answered, \u201CThey have seen all that is in my house. There is nothing
        in my storehouses that I did not show them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Isaiah said to Hezekiah, \u201CHear the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts: "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Behold, the days are coming, when all that is in your house, and
        that which your fathers have stored up till this day, shall be carried to
        Babylon. Nothing shall be left, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And some of your own sons, who will come from you, whom you will
        father, shall be taken away, and they shall be eunuchs in the palace of the
        king of Babylon.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Hezekiah said to Isaiah, \u201CThe word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        that you have spoken is good.\u201D For he thought, \u201CThere will be peace
        and security in my days.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Comfort for God\u2019s People"
      title: "Comfort for God\u2019s People"
      number: 1
      content: '    Comfort, comfort my people, says your God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "  Speak tenderly to Jerusalem,and cry to herthat her warfare[[COMMENT(0)]]
        is ended,that her iniquity is pardoned,that she has received from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        handdouble for all her sins.  "
      comments:
      - number: '40:2 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "  A voice cries:[[COMMENT(0)]]  \u201CIn the wilderness prepare the
        way of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;  make straight in the desert a highway
        for our God.  "
      comments:
      - number: '40:3 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  Every valley shall be lifted up,and every mountain and hill be
        made low;the uneven ground shall become level,and the rough places a plain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: The Word of God Stands Forever'
      title: The Word of God Stands Forever
      number: 5
      content: "  And the glory of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> shall be revealed,and
        all flesh shall see it together,  for the mouth of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has spoken.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "A voice says, \u201CCry!\u201DAnd I said,[[COMMENT(0)]] \u201CWhat
        shall I cry?\u201D  All flesh is grass,and all its beauty is like the flower
        of the field.  "
      comments:
      - number: '40:6 '
        content: 'Revocalization based on Dead Sea Scroll, Septuagint, Vulgate; Masoretic
          Text Or '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The grass withers, the flower fadeswhen the breath of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        blows on it;surely the people are grass.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The Greatness of God'
      title: The Greatness of God
      number: 8
      content: '  The grass withers, the flower fades,but the word of our God will
        stand forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Go on up to a high mountain,O Zion, herald of good news;[[COMMENT(0)]]lift
        up your voice with strength,O Jerusalem, herald of good news;lift it up,
        fear not;say to the cities of Judah,\u201CBehold your God!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '40:9 '
        content: 'Or Or '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  Behold, the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> comes with might,and
        his arm rules for him;  behold, his reward is with him,and his recompense
        before him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  He will tend his flock like a shepherd;  he will gather the lambs
        in his arms;  he will carry them in his bosom,and gently lead those that
        are with young.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  Who has measured the waters in the hollow of his handand marked
        off the heavens with a span,enclosed the dust of the earth in a measureand
        weighed the mountains in scalesand the hills in a balance?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  Who has measured[[COMMENT(0)]] the Spirit of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,or
        what man shows him his counsel?  '
      comments:
      - number: '40:13 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Whom did he consult,and who made him understand?  Who taught him
        the path of justice,and taught him knowledge,and showed him the way of understanding?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Behold, the nations are like a drop from a bucket,and are accounted
        as the dust on the scales;behold, he takes up the coastlands like fine dust.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Lebanon would not suffice for fuel,nor are its beasts enough for
        a burnt offering.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  All the nations are as nothing before him,they are accounted by
        him as less than nothing and emptiness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  To whom then will you liken God,  or what likeness compare with
        him?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  An idol! A craftsman casts it,and a goldsmith overlays it with
        goldand casts for it silver chains.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  He who is too impoverished for an offeringchooses wood[[COMMENT(0)]]
        that will not rot;he seeks out a skillful craftsmanto set up an idol that
        will not move.  '
      comments:
      - number: '40:20 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  Do you not know? Do you not hear?Has it not been told you from
        the beginning?Have you not understood from the foundations of the earth?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'It is he who sits above the circle of the earth,and its inhabitants
        are like grasshoppers;  who stretches out the heavens like a curtain,and
        spreads them like a tent to dwell in;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  who brings princes to nothing,and makes the rulers of the earth
        as emptiness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Scarcely are they planted, scarcely sown,scarcely has their stem
        taken root in the earth,when he blows on them, and they wither,  and the
        tempest carries them off like stubble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  To whom then will you compare me,that I should be like him? says
        the Holy One.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Lift up your eyes on high and see:who created these?  He who brings
        out their host by number,calling them all by name;by the greatness of his
        mightand because he is strong in power,not one is missing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Why do you say, O Jacob,and speak, O Israel,  \u201CMy way is hidden
        from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,  and my right is disregarded by my
        God\u201D?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Have you not known? Have you not heard?The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is the everlasting God,the Creator of the ends of the earth.He does not faint
        or grow weary;  his understanding is unsearchable.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'He gives power to the faint,and to him who has no might he increases
        strength.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Even youths shall faint and be weary,and young men shall fall exhausted;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: but they who wait for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> shall renew
        their strength;they shall mount up with wings like eagles;they shall run
        and not be weary;they shall walk and not faint.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Fear Not, for I Am with You'
      title: Fear Not, for I Am with You
      number: 1
      content: '    Listen to me in silence, O coastlands;let the peoples renew their
        strength;let them approach, then let them speak;let us together draw near
        for judgment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  Who stirred up one from the eastwhom victory meets at every step?[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        He gives up nations before him,so that he tramples kings underfoot;he makes
        them like dust with his sword,  like driven stubble with his bow.  '
      comments:
      - number: '41:2 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He pursues them and passes on safely,by paths his feet have not trod.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  Who has performed and done this,calling the generations from the
        beginning?  I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the first,and with the last;
        I am he.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  The coastlands have seen and are afraid;the ends of the earth tremble;they
        have drawn near and come.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Everyone helps his neighborand says to his brother, \u201CBe strong!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  The craftsman strengthens the goldsmith,and he who smooths with
        the hammer him who strikes the anvil,saying of the soldering, \u201CIt is
        good\u201D;and they strengthen it with nails so that it cannot be moved.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But you, Israel, my servant,Jacob, whom I have chosen,the offspring
        of Abraham, my friend;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "you whom I took from the ends of the earth,and called from its farthest
        corners,saying to you, \u201CYou are my servant,  I have chosen you and not
        cast you off\u201D;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'fear not, for I am with you;be not dismayed, for I am your God;I
        will strengthen you, I will help you,I will uphold you with my righteous
        right hand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  Behold, all who are incensed against youshall be put to shame and
        confounded;those who strive against youshall be as nothing and shall perish.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  You shall seek those who contend with you,but you shall not find
        them;  those who war against youshall be as nothing at all.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "For I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God,hold your right hand;it
        is I who say to you, \u201CFear not,I am the one who helps you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Fear not, you worm Jacob,you men of Israel!I am the one who helps
        you, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;your Redeemer is the Holy One
        of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  Behold, I make of you a threshing sledge,new, sharp, and having
        teeth;you shall thresh the mountains and crush them,and you shall make the
        hills like chaff;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  you shall winnow them, and the wind shall carry them away,and the
        tempest shall scatter them.  And you shall rejoice in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;in
        the Holy One of Israel you shall glory.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  When the poor and needy seek water,and there is none,and their
        tongue is parched with thirst,I the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will answer
        them;I the God of Israel will not forsake them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  I will open rivers on the bare heights,and fountains in the midst
        of the valleys.  I will make the wilderness a pool of water,and the dry land
        springs of water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  I will put in the wilderness the cedar,the acacia, the myrtle,
        and the olive.I will set in the desert the cypress,the plane and the pine
        together,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: The Futility of Idols'
      title: The Futility of Idols
      number: 20
      content: 'that they may see and know,may consider and understand together,that
        the hand of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has done this,the Holy One of
        Israel has created it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Set forth your case, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;bring your
        proofs, says the King of Jacob.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Let them bring them, and tell uswhat is to happen.Tell us the former
        things, what they are,that we may consider them,that we may know their outcome;or
        declare to us the things to come.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  Tell us what is to come hereafter,that we may know that you are
        gods;  do good, or do harm,that we may be dismayed and terrified.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '41:23 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Behold, you are nothing,and your work is less than nothing;an abomination
        is he who chooses you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  I stirred up one from the north, and he has come,  from the rising
        of the sun, and he shall call upon my name;he shall trample on rulers as
        on mortar,as the potter treads clay.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "  Who declared it from the beginning, that we might know,and beforehand,
        that we might say, \u201CHe is right\u201D?There was none who declared it,
        none who proclaimed,none who heard your words.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "  I was the first to say[[COMMENT(0)]] to Zion, \u201CBehold, here
        they are!\u201Dand I give to Jerusalem a herald of good news.  "
      comments:
      - number: '41:27 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '  But when I look, there is no one;among these there is no counselorwho,
        when I ask, gives an answer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '  Behold, they are all a delusion;their works are nothing;their metal
        images are empty wind.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The \u2019s Chosen Servant"
      title: "The \u2019s Chosen Servant"
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>    Behold my servant, whom I uphold,my
        chosen, in whom my soul delights;  I have put my Spirit upon him;  he will
        bring forth justice to the nations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He will not cry aloud or lift up his voice,or make it heard in the
        street;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  a bruised reed he will not break,and a faintly burning wick he
        will not quench;  he will faithfully bring forth justice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He will not grow faint or be discouraged[[COMMENT(0)]]till he has
        established justice in the earth;and the coastlands wait for his law.  '
      comments:
      - number: '42:4 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Thus says God, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,who created the heavens
        and stretched them out,who spread out the earth and what comes from it, 
        who gives breath to the people on itand spirit to those who walk in it:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CI am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>; I have called you[[COMMENT(0)]]
        in righteousness;I will take you by the hand and keep you;I will give you
        as a covenant for the people,  a light for the nations,  "
      comments:
      - number: '42:6 '
        content: The Hebrew for is singular; four times in this verse
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  to open the eyes that are blind,to bring out the prisoners from
        the dungeon,  from the prison those who sit in darkness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>; that is my name;  my glory
        I give to no other,nor my praise to carved idols.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Sing to the  a New Song'
      title: Sing to the  a New Song
      number: 9
      content: "Behold, the former things have come to pass,  and new things I now
        declare;before they spring forthI tell you of them.\u201D<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  Sing to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> a new song,his praise from
        the end of the earth,  you who go down to the sea, and all that fills it, 
        the coastlands and their inhabitants.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Let the desert and its cities lift up their voice,the villages that
        Kedar inhabits;let the habitants of Sela sing for joy,let them shout from
        the top of the mountains.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Let them give glory to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and declare
        his praise in the coastlands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> goes out like a mighty man,like
        a man of war he stirs up his zeal;he cries out, he shouts aloud,he shows
        himself mighty against his foes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For a long time I have held my peace;I have kept still and restrained
        myself;now I will cry out like a woman in labor;I will gasp and pant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  I will lay waste mountains and hills,and dry up all their vegetation;I
        will turn the rivers into islands,[[COMMENT(0)]]and dry up the pools.  '
      comments:
      - number: '42:15 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  And I will lead the blindin a way that they do not know,in paths
        that they have not knownI will guide them.I will turn the darkness before
        them into light,  the rough places into level ground.These are the things
        I do,and I do not forsake them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "17: Israel\u2019s Failure to Hear and See"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Failure to Hear and See"
      number: 17
      content: "  They are turned back and utterly put to shame,who trust in carved
        idols,who say to metal images,\u201CYou are our gods.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Hear, you deaf,and look, you blind, that you may see!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Who is blind but my servant,or deaf as my messenger whom I send?Who
        is blind as my dedicated one,[[COMMENT(0)]]or blind as the servant of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?  '
      comments:
      - number: '42:19 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  He sees many things, but does not observe them;  his ears are open,
        but he does not hear.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was pleased, for his righteousness\u2019
        sake,to magnify his law and make it glorious.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But this is a people plundered and looted;they are all of them trapped
        in holes  and hidden in prisons;they have become plunder with none to rescue,spoil
        with none to say, \u201CRestore!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Who among you will give ear to this,will attend and listen for the
        time to come?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Who gave up Jacob to the looter,and Israel to the plunderers?Was
        it not the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, against whom we have sinned,in whose
        ways they would not walk,and whose law they would not obey?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: So he poured on him the heat of his angerand the might of battle;it
        set him on fire all around, but he did not understand;it burned him up, but
        he did not take it to heart.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel\u2019s Only Savior"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Only Savior"
      number: 1
      content: "  But now thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,  he who created
        you, O Jacob,he who formed you, O Israel:  \u201CFear not, for I have redeemed
        you;  I have called you by name, you are mine.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  When you pass through the waters, I will be with you;and through
        the rivers, they shall not overwhelm you;  when you walk through fire you
        shall not be burned,and the flame shall not consume you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God,the Holy One of
        Israel, your Savior.  I give Egypt as your ransom,Cush and Seba in exchange
        for you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Because you are precious in my eyes,and honored, and I love you,I
        give men in return for you,peoples in exchange for your life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  Fear not, for I am with you;  I will bring your offspring from
        the east,and from the west I will gather you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I will say to the north, Give up,and to the south, Do not withhold;bring
        my sons from afarand my daughters from the end of the earth,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "everyone who is called by my name,whom I created for my glory,whom
        I formed and made.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Bring out the people who are blind, yet have eyes,who are deaf, yet
        have ears!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  All the nations gather together,and the peoples assemble.Who among
        them can declare this,and show us the former things?Let them bring their
        witnesses to prove them right,and let them hear and say, It is true.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "  \u201CYou are my witnesses,\u201D declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201Cand
        my servant whom I have chosen,that you may know and believe meand understand
        that I am he.  Before me no god was formed,nor shall there be any after me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  I, I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and besides me there is
        no savior.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "I declared and saved and proclaimed,when there was no strange god
        among you;and you are my witnesses,\u201D declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        \u201Cand I am God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Also henceforth I am he;there is none who can deliver from my hand;I
        work, and who can turn it back?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,your Redeemer, the Holy
        One of Israel:  \u201CFor your sake I send to Babylonand bring them all down
        as fugitives,  even the Chaldeans, in the ships in which they rejoice.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, your Holy One,the Creator of
        Israel, your King.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,  who makes a way in the
        sea,a path in the mighty waters,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'who brings forth chariot and horse,army and warrior;they lie down,
        they cannot rise,  they are extinguished, quenched like a wick:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "  \u201CRemember not the former things,nor consider the things of
        old.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  Behold, I am doing a new thing;now it springs forth, do you not
        perceive it?  I will make a way in the wilderness  and rivers in the desert.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The wild beasts will honor me,  the jackals and the ostriches,  for
        I give water in the wilderness,rivers in the desert,to give drink to my chosen
        people,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'the people whom I formed for myself  that they might declare my praise.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CYet you did not call upon me, O Jacob;but you have been weary
        of me, O Israel!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  You have not brought me your sheep for burnt offerings,or honored
        me with your sacrifices.I have not burdened you with offerings,  or wearied
        you with frankincense.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'You have not bought me sweet cane with money,or satisfied me with
        the fat of your sacrifices.But you have burdened me with your sins;you have
        wearied me with your iniquities.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CI, I am he  who blots out your transgressions for my own sake,and
        I will not remember your sins.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Put me in remembrance; let us argue together;set forth your case,
        that you may be proved right.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '  Your first father sinned,and your mediators transgressed against
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Therefore I will profane the princes of the sanctuary,and deliver
        Jacob to utter destructionand Israel to reviling.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel the \u2019s Chosen"
      title: "Israel the \u2019s Chosen"
      number: 1
      content: "<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  \u201CBut now hear, O Jacob my servant,Israel
        whom I have chosen!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who made you,  who formed
        you from the womb and will help you:  Fear not, O Jacob my servant,  Jeshurun
        whom I have chosen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  For I will pour water on the thirsty land,and streams on the dry
        ground;I will pour my Spirit upon your offspring,and my blessing on your
        descendants.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They shall spring up among the grass  like willows by flowing streams.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Besides Me There Is No God'
      title: Besides Me There Is No God
      number: 5
      content: "  This one will say, \u2018I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s,\u2019another
        will call on the name of Jacob,and another will write on his hand, \u2018The
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s,\u2019and name himself by the name of
        Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the King of Israeland
        his Redeemer, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts:  \u201CI am the first
        and I am the last;besides me there is no god.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  Who is like me? Let him proclaim it.[[COMMENT(0)]]Let him declare
        and set it before me,since I appointed an ancient people.Let them declare
        what is to come, and what will happen.  '
      comments:
      - number: '44:7 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '8: The Folly of Idolatry'
      title: The Folly of Idolatry
      number: 8
      content: "Fear not, nor be afraid;have I not told you from of old and declared
        it?  And you are my witnesses!  Is there a God besides me?There is no Rock;
        I know not any.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  All who fashion idols are nothing, and the things they delight
        in do not profit. Their witnesses neither see nor know, that they may be
        put to shame. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Who fashions a god or casts an idol that is profitable for nothing? '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Behold, all his companions shall be put to shame, and the craftsmen
        are only human. Let them all assemble, let them stand forth. They shall be
        terrified; they shall be put to shame together.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  The ironsmith takes a cutting tool and works it over the coals.
        He fashions it with hammers and works it with his strong arm. He becomes
        hungry, and his strength fails; he drinks no water and is faint. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The carpenter stretches a line; he marks it out with a pencil.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        He shapes it with planes and marks it with a compass. He shapes it into the
        figure of a man, with the beauty of a man, to dwell in a house. '
      comments:
      - number: '44:13 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He cuts down cedars, or he chooses a cypress tree or an oak and lets
        it grow strong among the trees of the forest. He plants a cedar and the rain
        nourishes it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then it becomes fuel for a man. He takes a part of it and warms himself;
        he kindles a fire and bakes bread. Also he makes a god and worships it; he
        makes it an idol and falls down before it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Half of it he burns in the fire. Over the half he eats meat; he roasts
        it and is satisfied. Also he warms himself and says, \u201CAha, I am warm,
        I have seen the fire!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And the rest of it he makes into a god, his idol, and falls down
        to it and worships it. He prays to it and says, \u201CDeliver me, for you
        are my god!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'They know not, nor do they discern, for he has shut their eyes, so
        that they cannot see, and their hearts, so that they cannot understand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "No one considers, nor is there knowledge or discernment to say, \u201CHalf
        of it I burned in the fire; I also baked bread on its coals; I roasted meat
        and have eaten. And shall I make the rest of it an abomination? Shall I fall
        down before a block of wood?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: The  Redeems Israel'
      title: The  Redeems Israel
      number: 20
      content: "He feeds on ashes; a deluded heart has led him astray, and he cannot
        deliver himself or say, \u201CIs there not a lie in my right hand?\u201D<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Remember these things, O Jacob,and Israel, for you are my servant;I
        formed you; you are my servant;  O Israel, you will not be forgotten by me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  I have blotted out your transgressions like a cloudand your sins
        like mist;return to me, for I have redeemed you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  Sing, O heavens, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has done it;shout,
        O depths of the earth;break forth into singing, O mountains,O forest, and
        every tree in it!For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has redeemed Jacob, 
        and will be glorified[[COMMENT(0)]] in Israel.  '
      comments:
      - number: '44:23 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, your Redeemer,  who formed
        you from the womb:  \u201CI am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, who made
        all things,  who alone stretched out the heavens,who spread out the earth
        by myself,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'who frustrates the signs of liarsand makes fools of diviners,  who
        turns wise men backand makes their knowledge foolish,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "  who confirms the word of his servantand fulfills the counsel of
        his messengers,who says of Jerusalem, \u2018She shall be inhabited,\u2019 
        and of the cities of Judah, \u2018They shall be built,and I will raise up
        their ruins\u2019;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "  who says to the deep, \u2018Be dry;I will dry up your rivers\u2019;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "who says of Cyrus, \u2018He is my shepherd,and he shall fulfill all
        my purpose\u2019;saying of Jerusalem, \u2018She shall be built,\u2019  and
        of the temple, \u2018Your foundation shall be laid.\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Cyrus, God\u2019s Instrument"
      title: "Cyrus, God\u2019s Instrument"
      number: 1
      content: '  Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to his anointed, to Cyrus, 
        whose right hand I have grasped,to subdue nations before himand to loose
        the belts of kings,to open doors before himthat gates may not be closed:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CI will go before youand level the exalted places,[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        I will break in pieces the doors of bronzeand cut through the bars of iron,  "
      comments:
      - number: '45:2 '
        content: 'Masoretic Text; Dead Sea Scroll, Septuagint '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  I will give you the treasures of darknessand the hoards in secret
        places,that you may know that it is I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,the
        God of Israel, who call you by your name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For the sake of my servant Jacob,and Israel my chosen,  I call you
        by your name,  I name you, though you do not know me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and there is no other,besides
        me there is no God;  I equip you, though you do not know me,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  that people may know, from the rising of the sunand from the west,
        that there is none besides me;I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and there
        is no other.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I form light and create darkness;I make well-being and create calamity;I
        am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, who does all these things.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "  \u201CShower, O heavens, from above,and let the clouds rain down
        righteousness;let the earth open, that salvation and righteousness may bear
        fruit;let the earth cause them both to sprout;I the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        have created it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "  \u201CWoe to him who strives with him who formed him,a pot among
        earthen pots!  Does the clay say to him who forms it, \u2018What are you
        making?\u2019or \u2018Your work has no handles\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Woe to him who says to a father, \u2018What are you begetting?\u2019or
        to a woman, \u2018With what are you in labor?\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,the Holy One of Israel,
        and the one who formed him:  \u201CAsk me of things to come;will you command
        me concerning my children and the work of my hands?[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '45:11 '
        content: A slight emendation yields ?
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  I made the earthand created man on it;it was my hands that stretched
        out the heavens,and I commanded all their host.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: The , the Only Savior'
      title: The , the Only Savior
      number: 13
      content: "  I have stirred him up in righteousness,  and I will make all his
        ways level;  he shall build my city  and set my exiles free,not for price
        or reward,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts.<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  \u201CThe wealth of Egypt
        and the merchandise of Cush,and the Sabeans, men of stature,shall come over
        to you and be yours;they shall follow you;they shall come over in chains
        and bow down to you.They will plead with you, saying:\u2018Surely God is
        in you, and there is no other,no god besides him.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  Truly, you are a God who hides himself,O God of Israel, the Savior.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  All of them are put to shame and confounded;the makers of idols
        go in confusion together.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But Israel is saved by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>with everlasting
        salvation;  you shall not be put to shame or confoundedto all eternity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "  For thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,who created the heavens(he
        is God!),who formed the earth and made it(he established it;he did not create
        it empty,  he formed it to be inhabited!):\u201CI am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and there is no other.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "  I did not speak in secret,in a land of darkness;I did not say to
        the offspring of Jacob,  \u2018Seek me in vain.\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]I the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> speak the truth;I declare what is right.  "
      comments:
      - number: '45:19 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "  \u201CAssemble yourselves and come;draw near together,you survivors
        of the nations!  They have no knowledgewho carry about their wooden idols, 
        and keep on praying to a godthat cannot save.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  Declare and present your case;let them take counsel together!Who
        told this long ago?Who declared it of old?Was it not I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?And
        there is no other god besides me,a righteous God and a Savior;there is none
        besides me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CTurn to me and be saved,  all the ends of the earth!For I am
        God, and there is no other.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "  By myself I have sworn;from my mouth has gone out in righteousnessa
        word that shall not return:  \u2018To me every knee shall bow,every tongue
        shall swear allegiance.\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '45:23 '
        content: 'Septuagint '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "  \u201COnly in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, it shall be said
        of me,are righteousness and strength;to him shall come and be ashamed  all
        who were incensed against him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "In the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> all the offspring of Israelshall
        be justified and shall glory.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Idols of Babylon and the One True God'
      title: The Idols of Babylon and the One True God
      number: 1
      content: '    Bel bows down; Nebo stoops;their idols are on beasts and livestock;these
        things you carry are borneas burdens on weary beasts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'They stoop; they bow down together;they cannot save the burden,but
        themselves go into captivity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CListen to me, O house of Jacob,all the remnant of the house
        of Israel,  who have been borne by me from before your birth,carried from
        the womb;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  even to your old age I am he,and to gray hairs I will carry you.I
        have made, and I will bear;I will carry and will save.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "  \u201CTo whom will you liken me and make me equal,and compare me,
        that we may be alike?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  Those who lavish gold from the purse,and weigh out silver in the
        scales,hire a goldsmith, and he makes it into a god;  then they fall down
        and worship!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  They lift it to their shoulders, they carry it,they set it in its
        place, and it stands there;  it cannot move from its place.If one cries to
        it, it does not answeror save him from his trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CRemember this and stand firm,recall it to mind, you transgressors,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'remember the former things of old;for I am God, and there is no other;I
        am God, and there is none like me,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "  declaring the end from the beginningand from ancient times things
        not yet done,saying, \u2018My counsel shall stand,and I will accomplish all
        my purpose,\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  calling a bird of prey from the east,the man of my counsel from
        a far country.  I have spoken, and I will bring it to pass;I have purposed,
        and I will do it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CListen to me, you stubborn of heart,you who are far from righteousness:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  I bring near my righteousness; it is not far off,and my salvation
        will not delay;  I will put salvation in Zion,for Israel my glory.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Humiliation of Babylon'
      title: The Humiliation of Babylon
      number: 1
      content: '    Come down and sit in the dust,O virgin daughter of Babylon; 
        sit on the ground without a throne,O daughter of the Chaldeans!  For you
        shall no more be calledtender and delicate.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Take the millstones and grind flour,  put off your veil,strip off
        your robe, uncover your legs,pass through the rivers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Your nakedness shall be uncovered,and your disgrace shall be seen.I
        will take vengeance,and I will spare no one.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "  Our Redeemer\u2014the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts is his
        name\u2014is the Holy One of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  Sit in silence, and go into darkness,O daughter of the Chaldeans;for
        you shall no more be called  the mistress of kingdoms.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  I was angry with my people;I profaned my heritage;I gave them into
        your hand;  you showed them no mercy;on the aged you made your yoke exceedingly
        heavy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "You said, \u201CI shall be mistress forever,\u201Dso that you did
        not lay these things to heartor remember their end.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Now therefore hear this, you lover of pleasures,  who sit securely,who
        say in your heart,  \u201CI am, and there is no one besides me;  I shall
        not sit as a widowor know the loss of children\u201D:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  These two things shall come to youin a moment, in one day;the loss
        of children and widowhoodshall come upon you in full measure,  in spite of
        your many sorceriesand the great power of your enchantments.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "You felt secure in your wickedness;you said, \u201CNo one sees me\u201D;your
        wisdom and your knowledge led you astray,and you said in your heart,  \u201CI
        am, and there is no one besides me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But evil shall come upon you,which you will not know how to charm
        away;disaster shall fall upon you,for which you will not be able to atone; 
        and ruin shall come upon you suddenly,of which you know nothing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  Stand fast in your enchantmentsand your many sorceries,with which
        you have labored from your youth;perhaps you may be able to succeed;perhaps
        you may inspire terror.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You are wearied with your many counsels;let them stand forth and
        save you,  those who divide the heavens,who gaze at the stars,who at the
        new moons make knownwhat shall come upon you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Behold, they are like stubble;  the fire consumes them;they cannot
        deliver themselvesfrom the power of the flame.No coal for warming oneself
        is this,no fire to sit before!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Such to you are those with whom you have labored,who have done business
        with you from your youth;they wander about, each in his own direction;there
        is no one to save you.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel Refined for God\u2019s Glory"
      title: "Israel Refined for God\u2019s Glory"
      number: 1
      content: '  Hear this, O house of Jacob,  who are called by the name of Israel,and
        who came from the waters of Judah,  who swear by the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>and
        confess the God of Israel,but not in truth or right.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For they call themselves after the holy city,  and stay themselves
        on the God of Israel;the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts is his name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CThe former things I declared of old;they went out from my mouth,
        and I announced them;then suddenly I did them, and they came to pass.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Because I know that you are obstinate,and your neck is an iron sinewand
        your forehead brass,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "  I declared them to you from of old,before they came to pass I announced
        them to you,lest you should say, \u2018My idol did them,my carved image and
        my metal image commanded them.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CYou have heard; now see all this;and will you not declare it?From
        this time forth I announce to you new things,hidden things that you have
        not known.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "They are created now, not long ago;before today you have never heard
        of them,lest you should say, \u2018Behold, I knew them.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'You have never heard, you have never known,from of old your ear has
        not been opened.For I knew that you would surely deal treacherously,and that
        from before birth you were called a rebel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "  \u201CFor my name\u2019s sake I defer my anger;for the sake of
        my praise I restrain it for you,that I may not cut you off.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Behold, I have refined you, but not as silver;  I have tried[[COMMENT(0)]]
        you in the furnace of affliction.  '
      comments:
      - number: '48:10 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: "11: The \u2019s Call to Israel"
      title: "The \u2019s Call to Israel"
      number: 11
      content: '  For my own sake, for my own sake, I do it,for how should my name[[COMMENT(0)]]
        be profaned?  My glory I will not give to another.<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  '
      comments:
      - number: '48:11 '
        content: 'Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CListen to me, O Jacob,and Israel, whom I called!I am he; I
        am the first,and I am the last.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'My hand laid the foundation of the earth,and my right hand spread
        out the heavens;  when I call to them,they stand forth together.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CAssemble, all of you, and listen!  Who among them has declared
        these things?The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> loves him;  he shall perform
        his purpose on Babylon,and his arm shall be against the Chaldeans.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  I, even I, have spoken and called him;I have brought him, and he
        will prosper in his way.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  Draw near to me, hear this:from the beginning I have not spoken
        in secret,from the time it came to be I have been there.\u201DAnd now the
        Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> has sent me, and his Spirit.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,your Redeemer, the Holy
        One of Israel:\u201CI am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God,who teaches
        you to profit,who leads you in the way you should go.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  Oh that you had paid attention to my commandments!  Then your peace
        would have been like a river,and your righteousness like the waves of the
        sea;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "  your offspring would have been like the sand,and your descendants
        like its grains;their name would never be cut offor destroyed from before
        me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "  Go out from Babylon, flee from Chaldea,declare this with a shout
        of joy, proclaim it,send it out to the end of the earth;say, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has redeemed his servant Jacob!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  They did not thirst when he led them through the deserts;  he made
        water flow for them from the rock;he split the rock and the water gushed
        out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "  \u201CThere is no peace,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        \u201Cfor the wicked.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Servant of the '
      title: 'The Servant of the '
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  Listen to me, O coastlands,and give
        attention, you peoples from afar.  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> called
        me from the womb,from the body of my mother he named my name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  He made my mouth like a sharp sword;  in the shadow of his hand
        he hid me;he made me a polished arrow;in his quiver he hid me away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And he said to me, \u201CYou are my servant,Israel, in whom I will
        be glorified.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '49:3 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "  But I said, \u201CI have labored in vain;I have spent my strength
        for nothing and vanity;yet surely my right is with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and
        my recompense with my God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "  And now the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says,he who formed me from
        the womb to be his servant,to bring Jacob back to him;and that Israel might
        be gathered to him\u2014for I am honored in the eyes of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and
        my God has become my strength\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "he says:\u201CIt is too light a thing that you should be my servantto
        raise up the tribes of Jacoband to bring back the preserved of Israel;  I
        will make you as a light for the nations,that my salvation may reach to the
        end of the earth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: The Restoration of Israel'
      title: The Restoration of Israel
      number: 7
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,  the Redeemer of Israel
        and his Holy One,  to one deeply despised, abhorred by the nation,the servant
        of rulers:  \u201CKings shall see and arise;princes, and they shall prostrate
        themselves;because of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, who is faithful,the
        Holy One of Israel, who has chosen you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  \u201CIn a time of favor
        I have answered you;in a day of salvation I have helped you;I will keep you
        and give youas a covenant to the people,to establish the land,  to apportion
        the desolate heritages,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "  saying to the prisoners, \u2018Come out,\u2019to those who are
        in darkness, \u2018Appear.\u2019  They shall feed along the ways;on all bare
        heights shall be their pasture;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  they shall not hunger or thirst,neither scorching wind nor sun
        shall strike them,for he who has pity on them will lead them,and by springs
        of water will guide them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  And I will make all my mountains a road,and my highways shall be
        raised up.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "  Behold, these shall come from afar,and behold, these from the north
        and from the west,[[COMMENT(0)]]and these from the land of Syene.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '49:12 '
        content: 'Hebrew Dead Sea Scroll; Masoretic Text '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  Sing for joy, O heavens, and exult, O earth;break forth, O mountains,
        into singing!For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  has comforted his peopleand
        will have compassion on his afflicted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But Zion said, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has forsaken
        me;my Lord has forgotten me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "  \u201CCan a woman forget her nursing child,that she should have
        no compassion on the son of her womb?Even these may forget,yet I will not
        forget you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Behold, I have engraved you on the palms of my hands;your walls are
        continually before me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Your builders make haste;[[COMMENT(0)]]  your destroyers and those
        who laid you waste go out from you.  '
      comments:
      - number: '49:17 '
        content: 'Dead Sea Scroll; Masoretic Text '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  Lift up your eyes around and see;they all gather, they come to
        you.  As I live, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,  you shall put
        them all on as an ornament;you shall bind them on as a bride does.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CSurely your waste and your desolate placesand your devastated
        land\u2014  surely now you will be too narrow for your inhabitants,and those
        who swallowed you up will be far away.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "  The children of your bereavementwill yet say in your ears:  \u2018The
        place is too narrow for me;make room for me to dwell in.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then you will say in your heart:\u2018Who has borne me these?  I
        was bereaved and barren,exiled and put away,but who has brought up these?Behold,
        I was left alone;from where have these come?\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Thus says the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>:\u201CBehold, I will
        lift up my hand to the nations,  and raise my signal to the peoples;  and
        they shall bring your sons in their arms,[[COMMENT(0)]]and your daughters
        shall be carried on their shoulders.  "
      comments:
      - number: '49:22 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "  Kings shall be your foster fathers,and their queens your nursing
        mothers.  With their faces to the ground they shall bow down to you,and lick
        the dust of your feet.Then you will know that I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>; 
        those who wait for me shall not be put to shame.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Can the prey be taken from the mighty,or the captives of a tyrant[[COMMENT(0)]]
        be rescued?  '
      comments:
      - number: '49:24 '
        content: 'Dead Sea Scroll, Syriac, Vulgate (see also verse 25); Masoretic
          Text '
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "For thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  \u201CEven the captives
        of the mighty shall be taken,and the prey of the tyrant be rescued,for I
        will contend with those who contend with you,and I will save your children.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "  I will make your oppressors eat their own flesh,and they shall
        be drunk with their own blood as with wine.Then all flesh shall knowthat
        I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your Savior,and your Redeemer, the Mighty
        One of Jacob.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel\u2019s Sin and the Servant\u2019s Obedience"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Sin and the Servant\u2019s Obedience"
      number: 1
      content: "  Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:\u201CWhere is your mother\u2019s
        certificate of divorce,with which I sent her away?Or which of my creditors
        is itto whom I have sold you?  Behold, for your iniquities you were sold,and
        for your transgressions your mother was sent away.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  Why, when I came, was there no man;why, when I called, was there
        no one to answer?  Is my hand shortened, that it cannot redeem?Or have I
        no power to deliver?  Behold, by my rebuke I dry up the sea,  I make the
        rivers a desert;  their fish stink for lack of waterand die of thirst.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "  I clothe the heavens with blacknessand make sackcloth their covering.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> has given methe tongue of those
        who are taught,that I may know how to sustain with a word  him who is weary.Morning
        by morning he awakens;he awakens my earto hear as those who are taught.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  The Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> has opened my ear,  and I was
        not rebellious;I turned not backward.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  I gave my back to those who strike,and my cheeks to those who pull
        out the beard;I hid not my facefrom disgrace and spitting.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> helps me;therefore I have
        not been disgraced;  therefore I have set my face like a flint,and I know
        that I shall not be put to shame.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  He who vindicates me is near.Who will contend with me?Let us stand
        up together.Who is my adversary?Let him come near to me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  Behold, the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> helps me;who will declare
        me guilty?Behold, all of them will wear out like a garment;the moth will
        eat them up.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Who among you fears the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>and obeys the
        voice of his servant?  Let him who walks in darknessand has no lighttrust
        in the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>and rely on his God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Behold, all you who kindle a fire,who equip yourselves with burning
        torches!Walk by the light of your fire,and by the torches that you have kindled! 
        This you have from my hand:you shall lie down in torment.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The \u2019s Comfort for Zion"
      title: "The \u2019s Comfort for Zion"
      number: 1
      content: "<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>    \u201CListen to me, you who pursue
        righteousness,you who seek the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:look to the rock
        from which you were hewn,and to the quarry from which you were dug.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Look to Abraham your fatherand to Sarah who bore you;for he was but
        one when I called him,that I might bless him and multiply him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  comforts Zion;he comforts all
        her waste placesand makes her wilderness like Eden,her desert like the garden
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;  joy and gladness will be found in her,thanksgiving
        and the voice of song.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "  \u201CGive attention to me, my people,and give ear to me, my nation; 
        for a law[[COMMENT(0)]] will go out from me,and I will set my justice for
        a light to the peoples.  "
      comments:
      - number: '51:4 '
        content: Or ; also verse 7
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  My righteousness draws near,my salvation has gone out,and my arms
        will judge the peoples;  the coastlands hope for me,and for my arm they wait.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  Lift up your eyes to the heavens,and look at the earth beneath; 
        for the heavens vanish like smoke,the earth will wear out like a garment,and
        they who dwell in it will die in like manner;[[COMMENT(0)]]  but my salvation
        will be forever,and my righteousness will never be dismayed.  '
      comments:
      - number: '51:6 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  \u201CListen to me, you who know righteousness,the people in whose
        heart is my law;  fear not the reproach of man,nor be dismayed at their revilings.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "  For the moth will eat them up like a garment,and the worm will
        eat them like wool,  but my righteousness will be forever,and my salvation
        to all generations.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  Awake, awake, put on strength,O arm of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;awake,
        as in days of old,the generations of long ago.Was it not you who cut Rahab
        in pieces,who pierced the dragon?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  Was it not you who dried up the sea,the waters of the great deep,who
        made the depths of the sea a wayfor the redeemed to pass over?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  And the ransomed of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> shall returnand
        come to Zion with singing;everlasting joy shall be upon their heads;they
        shall obtain gladness and joy,and sorrow and sighing shall flee away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CI, I am he who comforts you;who are you that you are afraid
        of man who dies,of the son of man who is made like grass,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and have forgotten the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, your Maker, 
        who stretched out the heavensand laid the foundations of the earth,and you
        fear continually all the daybecause of the wrath of the oppressor,when he
        sets himself to destroy?And where is the wrath of the oppressor?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  He who is bowed down shall speedily be released;he shall not die
        and go down to the pit,neither shall his bread be lacking.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God,  who stirs up the
        sea so that its waves roar\u2014the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts
        is his name.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  And I have put my words in your mouth  and covered you in the shadow
        of my hand,  establishing[[COMMENT(0)]] the heavensand laying the foundations
        of the earth,and saying to Zion, \u2018You are my people.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '51:16 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  Wake yourself, wake yourself,stand up, O Jerusalem,  you who have
        drunk from the hand of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>the cup of his wrath,who
        have drunk to the dregsthe bowl, the cup of staggering.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  There is none to guide heramong all the sons she has borne;there
        is none to take her by the handamong all the sons she has brought up.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "  These two things have happened to you\u2014who will console you?\u2014devastation
        and destruction, famine and sword;who will comfort you?[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '51:19 '
        content: 'Dead Sea Scroll, Septuagint, Syriac, Vulgate; Masoretic Text '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  Your sons have fainted;they lie at the head of every streetlike
        an antelope in a net;they are full of the wrath of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,the
        rebuke of your God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  Therefore hear this, you who are afflicted,who are drunk, but not
        with wine:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Thus says your Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,your God who
        pleads the cause of his people:\u201CBehold, I have taken from your hand
        the cup of staggering;the bowl of my wrath you shall drink no more;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "  and I will put it into the hand of your tormentors,  who have said
        to you,\u2018Bow down, that we may pass over\u2019;and you have made your
        back like the groundand like the street for them to pass over.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The \u2019s Coming Salvation"
      title: "The \u2019s Coming Salvation"
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>    Awake, awake,put on your strength,
        O Zion;  put on your beautiful garments,O Jerusalem, the holy city;  for
        there shall no more come into youthe uncircumcised and the unclean.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  Shake yourself from the dust and arise;be seated, O Jerusalem; 
        loose the bonds from your neck,O captive daughter of Zion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: \u201CYou were sold
        for nothing, and you shall be redeemed without money.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For thus says the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>: \u201CMy people
        went down at the first into Egypt to sojourn there, and the Assyrian oppressed
        them for nothing.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '52:4 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Now therefore what have I here,\u201D declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        \u201Cseeing that my people are taken away for nothing? Their rulers wail,\u201D
        declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u201Cand continually all the day
        my name is despised. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Therefore my people shall know my name. Therefore in that day they
        shall know that it is I who speak; here I am.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  How beautiful upon the mountainsare the feet of him who brings
        good news,who publishes peace, who brings good news of happiness,who publishes
        salvation,who says to Zion, \u201CYour God reigns.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The voice of your watchmen\u2014they lift up their voice;together
        they sing for joy;  for eye to eye they seethe return of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        to Zion.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  Break forth together into singing,  you waste places of Jerusalem,for
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has comforted his people;he has redeemed
        Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has bared his holy armbefore the
        eyes of all the nations,  and all the ends of the earth shall seethe salvation
        of our God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  Depart, depart, go out from there;touch no unclean thing;go out
        from the midst of her; purify yourselves,  you who bear the vessels of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: He Was Pierced for Our Transgressions'
      title: He Was Pierced for Our Transgressions
      number: 12
      content: 'For you shall not go out in haste,and you shall not go in flight, 
        for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will go before you,  and the God of Israel
        will be your rear guard.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Behold, my servant shall act wisely;[[COMMENT(0)]]he shall be high
        and lifted up,and shall be exalted.  '
      comments:
      - number: '52:13 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "As many were astonished at you\u2014  his appearance was so marred,
        beyond human semblance,and his form beyond that of the children of mankind\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: so shall he sprinkle[[COMMENT(0)]] many nations.  Kings shall shut
        their mouths because of him,  for that which has not been told them they
        see,and that which they have not heard they understand.
      comments:
      - number: '52:15 '
        content: 'Or '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '    Who has believed what he has heard from us?[[COMMENT(0)]]And
        to whom has the arm of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> been revealed?  '
      comments:
      - number: '53:1 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For he grew up before him like a young plant,  and like a root out
        of dry ground;  he had no form or majesty that we should look at him,and
        no beauty that we should desire him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  He was despised and rejected[[COMMENT(0)]] by men,a man of sorrows
        and acquainted with grief;and as one from whom men hide their faceshe was
        despised, and we esteemed him not.  '
      comments:
      - number: '53:3 '
        content: 'Or Or ; also verse 4Or Or ; also verse 4Or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  Surely he has borne our griefsand carried our sorrows;yet we esteemed
        him stricken,  smitten by God, and afflicted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  But he was pierced for our transgressions;he was crushed for our
        iniquities;upon him was the chastisement that brought us peace,  and with
        his wounds we are healed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "  All we like sheep have gone astray;we have turned\u2014every one\u2014to
        his own way;  and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has laid on himthe iniquity
        of us all.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He was oppressed, and he was afflicted,  yet he opened not his mouth; 
        like a lamb that is led to the slaughter,and like a sheep that before its
        shearers is silent,so he opened not his mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'By oppression and judgment he was taken away;and as for his generation,
        who consideredthat he was cut off out of the land of the living,stricken
        for the transgression of my people?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And they made his grave with the wicked  and with a rich man in his
        death,although he had done no violence,and there was no deceit in his mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Yet it was the will of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to crush him;he
        has put him to grief;[[COMMENT(0)]]  when his soul makes an offering for
        guilt,he shall see his offspring; he shall prolong his days;  the will of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> shall prosper in his hand.  '
      comments:
      - number: '53:10 '
        content: 'Or Or '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Out of the anguish of his soul he shall see[[COMMENT(0)]] and be
        satisfied;by his knowledge shall the righteous one, my servant,  make many
        to be accounted righteous,  and he shall bear their iniquities.  '
      comments:
      - number: '53:11 '
        content: 'Masoretic Text; Dead Sea Scroll '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  Therefore I will divide him a portion with the many,[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        and he shall divide the spoil with the strong,because he poured out his soul
        to deathand was numbered with the transgressors;  yet he bore the sin of
        many,and makes intercession for the transgressors.'
      comments:
      - number: '53:12 '
        content: 'Or Or '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Eternal Covenant of Peace'
      title: The Eternal Covenant of Peace
      number: 1
      content: "    \u201CSing, O barren one, who did not bear;break forth into singing
        and cry aloud,you who have not been in labor!For the children of the desolate
        one will be morethan the children of her who is married,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "  \u201CEnlarge the place of your tent,and let the curtains of your
        habitations be stretched out;do not hold back; lengthen your cordsand strengthen
        your stakes.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  For you will spread abroad to the right and to the left,and your
        offspring will possess the nationsand will people the desolate cities.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CFear not, for you will not be ashamed;be not confounded, for
        you will not be disgraced;for you will forget the shame of your youth,and
        the reproach of your widowhood you will remember no more.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  For your Maker is your husband,the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts is his name;  and the Holy One of Israel is your Redeemer,  the
        God of the whole earth he is called.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has called youlike a wife deserted
        and grieved in spirit,like a wife of youth when she is cast off,says your
        God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  For a brief moment I deserted you,but with great compassion I will
        gather you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "  In overflowing anger for a momentI hid my face from you,  but with
        everlasting love I will have compassion on you,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        your Redeemer.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThis is like the days of Noah[[COMMENT(0)]] to me:as I swore
        that the waters of Noahshould no more go over the earth,so I have sworn that
        I will not be angry with you,and will not rebuke you.  "
      comments:
      - number: '54:9 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For the mountains may departand the hills be removed,but my steadfast
        love shall not depart from you,and my covenant of peace shall not be removed,\u201Dsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, who has compassion on you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "  \u201CO afflicted one, storm-tossed and not comforted,behold, I
        will set your stones in antimony,  and lay your foundations with sapphires.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '54:11 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I will make your pinnacles of agate,[[COMMENT(0)]]your gates of carbuncles,and
        all your wall of precious stones.  '
      comments:
      - number: '54:12 '
        content: 'Or , or Or '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  All your children shall be taught by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, 
        and great shall be the peace of your children.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'In righteousness you shall be established;you shall be far from oppression,
        for you shall not fear;and from terror, for it shall not come near you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  If anyone stirs up strife,it is not from me;whoever stirs up strife
        with youshall fall because of you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Behold, I have created the smithwho blows the fire of coalsand produces
        a weapon for its purpose.I have also created the ravager to destroy;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "no weapon that is fashioned against you shall succeed,and you shall
        refute every tongue that rises against you in judgment.This is the heritage
        of the servants of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  and their vindication[[COMMENT(0)]]
        from me, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '54:17 '
        content: 'Or '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Compassion of the '
      title: 'The Compassion of the '
      number: 1
      content: "<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>    \u201CCome, everyone who thirsts,come
        to the waters;and he who has no money,  come, buy and eat!Come, buy wine
        and milkwithout money and without price.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  Why do you spend your money for that which is not bread,and your
        labor for that which does not satisfy?Listen diligently to me, and eat what
        is good,and delight yourselves in rich food.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Incline your ear, and come to me;  hear, that your soul may live; 
        and I will make with you an everlasting covenant,  my steadfast, sure love
        for David.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  Behold, I made him a witness to the peoples,  a leader and commander
        for the peoples.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  Behold, you shall call a nation that you do not know,and a nation
        that did not know you shall run to you,because of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, and of the Holy One of Israel,  for he has glorified you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "  \u201CSeek the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> while he may be found;call
        upon him while he is near;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'let the wicked forsake his way,and the unrighteous man his thoughts;let
        him return to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, that he may have compassion
        on him,and to our God, for he will abundantly pardon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For my thoughts are not your thoughts,neither are your ways my ways,
        declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  For as the heavens are higher than the earth,so are my ways higher
        than your waysand my thoughts than your thoughts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "  \u201CFor as the rain and the snow come down from heavenand do
        not return there but water the earth,making it bring forth and sprout,  giving
        seed to the sower and bread to the eater,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'so shall my word be that goes out from my mouth;it shall not return
        to me empty,but it shall accomplish that which I purpose,and shall succeed
        in the thing for which I sent it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "  \u201CFor you shall go out in joyand be led forth in peace;  the
        mountains and the hills before youshall break forth into singing,and all
        the trees of the field shall clap their hands.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  Instead of the thorn shall come up the cypress;instead of the brier
        shall come up the myrtle;and it shall make a name for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,an
        everlasting sign that shall not be cut off.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Salvation for Foreigners'
      title: Salvation for Foreigners
      number: 1
      content: "  Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:\u201CKeep justice, and
        do righteousness,  for soon my salvation will come,and my righteousness be
        revealed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Blessed is the man who does this,and the son of man who holds it
        fast,  who keeps the Sabbath, not profaning it,and keeps his hand from doing
        any evil.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Let not the foreigner who has joined himself to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        say,\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will surely separate me from his
        people\u201D;and let not the eunuch say,\u201CBehold, I am a dry tree.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:\u201CTo the eunuchs
        who keep my Sabbaths,who choose the things that please meand hold fast my
        covenant,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  I will give in my house and within my wallsa monument and a namebetter
        than sons and daughters;  I will give them an everlasting namethat shall
        not be cut off.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CAnd the foreigners who join themselves to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,to
        minister to him, to love the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and
        to be his servants,everyone who keeps the Sabbath and does not profane it,and
        holds fast my covenant\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  these I will bring to my holy mountain,and make them joyful in
        my house of prayer;  their burnt offerings and their sacrificeswill be accepted
        on my altar;for my house shall be called a house of prayerfor all peoples.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: "8: Israel\u2019s Irresponsible Leaders"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Irresponsible Leaders"
      number: 8
      content: "The Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>,  who gathers the outcasts of
        Israel, declares,  \u201CI will gather yet others to himbesides those already
        gathered.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "  All you beasts of the field, come to devour\u2014all you beasts
        in the forest.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  His watchmen are blind;they are all without knowledge;they are
        all silent dogs;they cannot bark,dreaming, lying down,loving to slumber.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  The dogs have a mighty appetite;they never have enough.But they
        are shepherds who have no understanding;they have all turned to their own
        way,  each to his own gain, one and all.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "  \u201CCome,\u201D they say, \u201Clet me get wine;let us fill ourselves
        with strong drink;  and tomorrow will be like this day,great beyond measure.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel\u2019s Futile Idolatry"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Futile Idolatry"
      number: 1
      content: '  The righteous man perishes,and no one lays it to heart;  devout
        men are taken away,while no one understands.For the righteous man is taken
        away from calamity;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  he enters into peace;they rest in their bedswho walk in their uprightness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But you, draw near,sons of the sorceress,  offspring of the adulterer
        and the loose woman.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Whom are you mocking?Against whom do you open your mouth wideand
        stick out your tongue?Are you not children of transgression,  the offspring
        of deceit,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'you who burn with lust among the oaks,[[COMMENT(0)]]under every green
        tree,  who slaughter your children in the valleys,under the clefts of the
        rocks?  '
      comments:
      - number: '57:5 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Among the smooth stones of the valley is your portion;they, they,
        are your lot;to them you have poured out a drink offering,you have brought
        a grain offering.Shall I relent for these things?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  On a high and lofty mountainyou have set your bed,and there you
        went up to offer sacrifice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Behind the door and the doorpostyou have set up your memorial;for,
        deserting me, you have uncovered your bed,you have gone up to it,  you have
        made it wide;and you have made a covenant for yourself with them,you have
        loved their bed,you have looked on nakedness.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '57:8 '
        content: 'Or (see 56:5); Hebrew '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'You journeyed to the king with oiland multiplied your perfumes; 
        you sent your envoys far off,and sent down even to Sheol.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "You were wearied with the length of your way,  but you did not say,
        \u201CIt is hopeless\u201D;you found new life for your strength,and so you
        were not faint.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '57:10 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  Whom did you dread and fear,  so that you lied,and did not remember
        me,did not lay it to heart?  Have I not held my peace, even for a long time,and
        you do not fear me?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I will declare your righteousness and your deeds,but they will not
        profit you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Comfort for the Contrite'
      title: Comfort for the Contrite
      number: 13
      content: '  When you cry out, let your collection of idols deliver you!The
        wind will carry them all off,a breath will take them away.  But he who takes
        refuge in me shall possess the landand shall inherit my holy mountain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And it shall be said,  \u201CBuild up, build up, prepare the way,remove
        every obstruction from my people\u2019s way.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For thus says the One who is high and lifted up,who inhabits eternity,
        whose name is Holy:  \u201CI dwell in the high and holy place,and also with
        him who is of a contrite and lowly spirit,  to revive the spirit of the lowly,and
        to revive the heart of the contrite.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  For I will not contend forever,nor will I always be angry;for the
        spirit would grow faint before me,and the breath of life that I made.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Because of the iniquity of his unjust gain I was angry,I struck him;
        I hid my face and was angry,but he went on backsliding in the way of his
        own heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'I have seen his ways, but I will heal him;I will lead him and restore
        comfort to him and his mourners,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "  creating the fruit of the lips.  Peace, peace, to the far and to
        the near,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,  \u201Cand I will heal
        him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  But the wicked are like the tossing sea;for it cannot be quiet,and
        its waters toss up mire and dirt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "  There is no peace,\u201D says my God, \u201Cfor the wicked.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: True and False Fasting'
      title: True and False Fasting
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CCry aloud; do not hold back;  lift up your voice like a trumpet; 
        declare to my people their transgression,to the house of Jacob their sins.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  Yet they seek me dailyand delight to know my ways,as if they were
        a nation that did righteousnessand did not forsake the judgment of their
        God;they ask of me righteous judgments;they delight to draw near to God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "  \u2018Why have we fasted, and you see it not?Why have we humbled
        ourselves, and you take no knowledge of it?\u2019Behold, in the day of your
        fast you seek your own pleasure,[[COMMENT(0)]]  and oppress all your workers.  "
      comments:
      - number: '58:3 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Behold, you fast only to quarrel and to fightand to hit with a wicked
        fist.Fasting like yours this daywill not make your voice to be heard on high.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  Is such the fast that I choose,  a day for a person to humble himself?Is
        it to bow down his head like a reed,and to spread sackcloth and ashes under
        him?Will you call this a fast,and a day acceptable to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CIs not this the fast that I choose:  to loose the bonds of
        wickedness,to undo the straps of the yoke,to let the oppressed[[COMMENT(0)]]
        go free,and to break every yoke?  "
      comments:
      - number: '58:6 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Is it not to share your bread with the hungryand bring the homeless
        poor into your house;when you see the naked, to cover him,  and not to hide
        yourself from your own flesh?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  Then shall your light break forth like the dawn,  and your healing
        shall spring up speedily;  your righteousness shall go before you;  the glory
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> shall be your rear guard.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then you shall call, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will answer;you
        shall cry, and he will say, \u2018Here I am.\u2019If you take away the yoke
        from your midst,  the pointing of the finger, and speaking wickedness,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  if you pour yourself out for the hungryand satisfy the desire of
        the afflicted,  then shall your light rise in the darknessand your gloom
        be as the noonday.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will guide you continuallyand
        satisfy your desire in scorched placesand make your bones strong;and you
        shall be like a watered garden,like a spring of water,whose waters do not
        fail.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  And your ancient ruins shall be rebuilt;you shall raise up the
        foundations of many generations;you shall be called the repairer of the breach,the
        restorer of streets to dwell in.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  \u201CIf you turn back your foot from the Sabbath,from doing your
        pleasure[[COMMENT(0)]] on my holy day,and call the Sabbath a delightand the
        holy day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> honorable;if you honor it, not
        going your own ways,or seeking your own pleasure, or talking idly;  "
      comments:
      - number: '58:13 '
        content: 'Or Or Hebrew '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "then you shall take delight in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, 
        and I will make you ride on the heights of the earth;[[COMMENT(0)]]  I will
        feed you with the heritage of Jacob your father,  for the mouth of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has spoken.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '58:14 '
        content: 'Or '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Evil and Oppression'
      title: Evil and Oppression
      number: 1
      content: "  Behold, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s hand is not shortened,
        that it cannot save,or his ear dull, that it cannot hear;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  but your iniquities have made a separationbetween you and your
        God,and your sins have hidden his face from youso that he does not hear.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  For your hands are defiled with bloodand your fingers with iniquity;your
        lips have spoken lies;your tongue mutters wickedness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  No one enters suit justly;no one goes to law honestly;they rely
        on empty pleas, they speak lies,  they conceive mischief and give birth to
        iniquity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They hatch adders\u2019 eggs;they weave the spider\u2019s web;he
        who eats their eggs dies,and from one that is crushed a viper is hatched.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  Their webs will not serve as clothing;men will not cover themselves
        with what they make.Their works are works of iniquity,and deeds of violence
        are in their hands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  Their feet run to evil,and they are swift to shed innocent blood;their
        thoughts are thoughts of iniquity;desolation and destruction are in their
        highways.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The way of peace they do not know,and there is no justice in their
        paths;they have made their roads crooked;  no one who treads on them knows
        peace.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Therefore justice is far from us,and righteousness does not overtake
        us;  we hope for light, and behold, darkness,and for brightness, but we walk
        in gloom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  We grope for the wall like the blind;we grope like those who have
        no eyes;we stumble at noon as in the twilight,  among those in full vigor
        we are like dead men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'We all growl like bears;  we moan and moan like doves;  we hope for
        justice, but there is none;for salvation, but it is far from us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For our transgressions are multiplied before you,and our sins testify
        against us;for our transgressions are with us,and we know our iniquities:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Judgment and Redemption'
      title: Judgment and Redemption
      number: 13
      content: 'transgressing, and denying the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and turning
        back from following our God,  speaking oppression and revolt,conceiving and
        uttering from the heart lying words.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  Justice is turned back,and righteousness stands far away;for truth
        has stumbled in the public squares,and uprightness cannot enter.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Truth is lacking,and he who departs from evil makes himself a prey.The
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> saw it, and it displeased him[[COMMENT(0)]]that
        there was no justice.  '
      comments:
      - number: '59:15 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  He saw that there was no man,and wondered that there was no one
        to intercede;then his own arm brought him salvation,and his righteousness
        upheld him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  He put on righteousness as a breastplate,and a helmet of salvation
        on his head;he put on garments of vengeance for clothing,and wrapped himself
        in zeal as a cloak.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  According to their deeds, so will he repay,wrath to his adversaries,
        repayment to his enemies;  to the coastlands he will render repayment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  So they shall fear the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        from the west,and his glory from the rising of the sun;  for he will come
        like a rushing stream,[[COMMENT(0)]]which the wind of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        drives.  '
      comments:
      - number: '59:19 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "  \u201CAnd a Redeemer will come to Zion,to those in Jacob who turn
        from transgression,\u201D declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CAnd as for me, this is my covenant with them,\u201D says the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: \u201CMy Spirit that is upon you, and my words
        that I have put in your mouth, shall not depart out of your mouth, or out
        of the mouth of your offspring, or out of the mouth of your children\u2019s
        offspring,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u201Cfrom this time
        forth and forevermore.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Future Glory of Israel'
      title: The Future Glory of Israel
      number: 1
      content: '    Arise, shine, for your light has come,and the glory of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has risen upon you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For behold, darkness shall cover the earth,and thick darkness the
        peoples;but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will arise upon you,and his glory
        will be seen upon you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  And nations shall come to your light,and kings to the brightness
        of your rising.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  Lift up your eyes all around, and see;they all gather together,
        they come to you;  your sons shall come from afar,and your daughters shall
        be carried on the hip.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then you shall see and be radiant;your heart shall thrill and exult,[[COMMENT(0)]]because
        the abundance of the sea shall be turned to you,  the wealth of the nations
        shall come to you.  '
      comments:
      - number: '60:5 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'A multitude of camels shall cover you,the young camels of Midian
        and Ephah;all those from Sheba shall come.  They shall bring gold and frankincense,and
        shall bring good news, the praises of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'All the flocks of Kedar shall be gathered to you;the rams of Nebaioth
        shall minister to you;  they shall come up with acceptance on my altar, 
        and I will beautify my beautiful house.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Who are these that fly like a cloud,and like doves to their windows?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For the coastlands shall hope for me,  the ships of Tarshish first, 
        to bring your children from afar,their silver and gold with them,for the
        name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God,and for the Holy One of
        Israel,because he has made you beautiful.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  Foreigners shall build up your walls,and their kings shall minister
        to you;for in my wrath I struck you,but in my favor I have had mercy on you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  Your gates shall be open continually;day and night they shall not
        be shut,  that people may bring to you the wealth of the nations,with their
        kings led in procession.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  For the nation and kingdomthat will not serve you shall perish;those
        nations shall be utterly laid waste.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  The glory of Lebanon shall come to you,the cypress, the plane,
        and the pine,to beautify the place of my sanctuary,and I will make the place
        of my feet glorious.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  The sons of those who afflicted youshall come bending low to you, 
        and all who despised youshall bow down at your feet;  they shall call you
        the City of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,the Zion of the Holy One of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  Whereas you have been forsaken and hated,with no one passing through, 
        I will make you majestic forever,a joy from age to age.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  You shall suck the milk of nations;you shall nurse at the breast
        of kings;and you shall know that I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, am your
        Saviorand your Redeemer, the Mighty One of Jacob.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Instead of bronze I will bring gold,and instead of iron I will bring
        silver;instead of wood, bronze,instead of stones, iron.I will make your overseers
        peace  and your taskmasters righteousness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  Violence shall no more be heard in your land,devastation or destruction
        within your borders;  you shall call your walls Salvation,and your gates
        Praise.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  The sun shall be no moreyour light by day,nor for brightness shall
        the moongive you light;[[COMMENT(0)]]but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will be your everlasting light,and your God will be your glory.  '
      comments:
      - number: '60:19 '
        content: 'Masoretic Text; Dead Sea Scroll, Septuagint, Targum add Or '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Your sun shall no more go down,nor your moon withdraw itself;for
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be your everlasting light,and your days
        of mourning shall be ended.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  Your people shall all be righteous;  they shall possess the land
        forever,  the branch of my planting, the work of my hands,that I might be
        glorified.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '60:21 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  The least one shall become a clan,and the smallest one a mighty
        nation;  I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;in its time I will hasten it.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Year of the \u2019s Favor"
      title: "The Year of the \u2019s Favor"
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>    The Spirit of the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>
        is upon me,because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has anointed meto bring
        good news to the poor;[[COMMENT(0)]]he has sent me to bind up the brokenhearted,to
        proclaim liberty to the captives,and the opening of the prison to those who
        are bound;  '
      comments:
      - number: '61:1 '
        content: 'Or Or [of the eyes] ; Septuagint '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "  to proclaim the year of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        favor,  and the day of vengeance of our God;to comfort all who mourn;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "to grant to those who mourn in Zion\u2014  to give them a beautiful
        headdress instead of ashes,  the oil of gladness instead of mourning,the
        garment of praise instead of a faint spirit;  that they may be called oaks
        of righteousness,the planting of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, that he
        may be glorified.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '61:3 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  They shall build up the ancient ruins;they shall raise up the former
        devastations;they shall repair the ruined cities,the devastations of many
        generations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  Strangers shall stand and tend your flocks;foreigners shall be
        your plowmen and vinedressers;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  but you shall be called the priests of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;they
        shall speak of you as the ministers of our God;  you shall eat the wealth
        of the nations,and in their glory you shall boast.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  Instead of your shame there shall be a double portion;instead of
        dishonor they shall rejoice in their lot;therefore in their land they shall
        possess a double portion;they shall have everlasting joy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  For I the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> love justice;I hate robbery
        and wrong;[[COMMENT(0)]]  I will faithfully give them their recompense, 
        and I will make an everlasting covenant with them.  '
      comments:
      - number: '61:8 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Their offspring shall be known among the nations,and their descendants
        in the midst of the peoples;all who see them shall acknowledge them,that
        they are an offspring the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has blessed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  I will greatly rejoice in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;my soul
        shall exult in my God,  for he has clothed me with the garments of salvation;he
        has covered me with the robe of righteousness,as a bridegroom decks himself
        like a priest with a beautiful headdress,  and as a bride adorns herself
        with her jewels.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: For as the earth brings forth its sprouts,and as a garden causes what
        is sown in it to sprout up,so the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> will cause
        righteousness and praiseto sprout up before all the nations.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Zion\u2019s Coming Salvation"
      title: "Zion\u2019s Coming Salvation"
      number: 1
      content: "    For Zion\u2019s sake I will not keep silent,and for Jerusalem\u2019s
        sake I will not be quiet,  until her righteousness goes forth as brightness,and
        her salvation as a burning torch.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  The nations shall see your righteousness,and all the kings your
        glory,  and you shall be called by a new namethat the mouth of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will give.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You shall be a crown of beauty in the hand of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and
        a royal diadem in the hand of your God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  You shall no more be termed Forsaken,[[COMMENT(0)]]and your land
        shall no more be termed Desolate,  but you shall be called My Delight Is
        in Her,and your land Married;for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> delights
        in you,and your land shall be married.  '
      comments:
      - number: '62:4 '
        content: 'Hebrew Hebrew Hebrew Hebrew '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For as a young man marries a young woman,so shall your sons marry
        you,and as the bridegroom rejoices over the bride,so shall your God rejoice
        over you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'On your walls, O Jerusalem,I have set watchmen;all the day and all
        the nightthey shall never be silent.You who put the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        in remembrance,take no rest,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and give him no restuntil he establishes Jerusalemand makes it a
        praise in the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has sworn by his right handand by
        his mighty arm:\u201CI will not again give your grainto be food for your
        enemies,  and foreigners shall not drink your winefor which you have labored;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "but those who garner it shall eat itand praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and
        those who gather it shall drink itin the courts of my sanctuary.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '62:9 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Go through, go through the gates;  prepare the way for the people; 
        build up, build up the highway;clear it of stones;  lift up a signal over
        the peoples.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Behold, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has proclaimedto the end
        of the earth:  Say to the daughter of Zion,  \u201CBehold, your salvation
        comes;behold, his reward is with him,and his recompense before him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  And they shall be called The Holy People,The Redeemed of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>; 
        and you shall be called Sought Out,A City Not Forsaken.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The \u2019s Day of Vengeance"
      title: "The \u2019s Day of Vengeance"
      number: 1
      content: "<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  Who is this who comes from Edom,in crimsoned
        garments from Bozrah,he who is splendid in his apparel,  marching in the
        greatness of his strength?\u201CIt is I, speaking in righteousness,mighty
        to save.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Why is your apparel red,and your garments like his who treads in
        the winepress?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "  \u201CI have trodden the winepress alone,  and from the peoples
        no one was with me;I trod them in my angerand trampled them in my wrath;their
        lifeblood[[COMMENT(0)]] spattered on my garments,and stained all my apparel.  "
      comments:
      - number: '63:3 '
        content: Or ; also verse 6
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  For the day of vengeance was in my heart,and my year of redemption[[COMMENT(0)]]
        had come.  '
      comments:
      - number: '63:4 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I looked, but there was no one to help;I was appalled, but there
        was no one to uphold;so my own arm brought me salvation,and my wrath upheld
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "6: The \u2019s Mercy Remembered"
      title: "The \u2019s Mercy Remembered"
      number: 6
      content: "I trampled down the peoples in my anger;  I made them drunk in my
        wrath,and I poured out their lifeblood on the earth.\u201D<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I will recount the steadfast love of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,the
        praises of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,according to all that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has granted us,  and the great goodness to the house of Israelthat he has
        granted them according to his compassion,according to the abundance of his
        steadfast love.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For he said, \u201CSurely they are my people,children who will not
        deal falsely.\u201DAnd he became their Savior.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  In all their affliction he was afflicted,[[COMMENT(0)]]and the
        angel of his presence saved them;  in his love and in his pity he redeemed
        them;  he lifted them up and carried them all the days of old.  '
      comments:
      - number: '63:9 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  But they rebelled  and grieved his Holy Spirit;therefore he turned
        to be their enemy,and himself fought against them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then he remembered the days of old,of Moses and his people.[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        Where is he who brought them up out of the seawith the shepherds of his flock?Where
        is he who put in the midst of themhis Holy Spirit,  '
      comments:
      - number: '63:11 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'who caused his glorious armto go at the right hand of Moses,  who
        divided the waters before them  to make for himself an everlasting name,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'who led them through the depths?Like a horse in the desert,they did
        not stumble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Prayer for Mercy'
      title: Prayer for Mercy
      number: 14
      content: 'Like livestock that go down into the valley,  the Spirit of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        gave them rest.So you led your people,  to make for yourself a glorious name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  Look down from heaven and see,  from your holy and beautiful[[COMMENT(0)]]
        habitation.Where are your zeal and your might?The stirring of your inner
        parts and your compassionare held back from me.  '
      comments:
      - number: '63:15 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For you are our Father,though Abraham does not know us,and Israel
        does not acknowledge us;you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, are our Father, 
        our Redeemer from of old is your name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, why do you make us wander from your
        waysand harden our heart, so that we fear you not?  Return for the sake of
        your servants,the tribes of your heritage.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  Your holy people held possession for a little while;[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        our adversaries have trampled down your sanctuary.  '
      comments:
      - number: '63:18 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  We have become like those over whom you have never ruled,like those
        who are not called by your name.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "    Oh that you would rend the heavens and come down,  that the mountains
        might quake at your presence\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "  [[COMMENT(0)]] as when fire kindles brushwoodand the fire causes
        water to boil\u2014  to make your name known to your adversaries,and that
        the nations might tremble at your presence!  "
      comments:
      - number: '64:2 '
        content: '  Ch 64:1 in Hebrew  '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  When you did awesome things that we did not look for,you came down,
        the mountains quaked at your presence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  From of old no one has heardor perceived by the ear,  no eye has
        seen a God besides you,who acts for those who wait for him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You meet him who joyfully works righteousness,those who remember
        you in your ways.Behold, you were angry, and we sinned;in our sins we have
        been a long time, and shall we be saved?[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '64:5 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  We have all become like one who is unclean,and all our righteous
        deeds are like a polluted garment.  We all fade like a leaf,and our iniquities,
        like the wind, take us away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  There is no one who calls upon your name,who rouses himself to
        take hold of you;for you have hidden your face from us,and have made us melt
        in[[COMMENT(0)]] the hand of our iniquities.  '
      comments:
      - number: '64:7 '
        content: 'Masoretic Text; Septuagint, Syriac, Targum '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  But now, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you are our Father;  we
        are the clay, and you are our potter;  we are all the work of your hand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  Be not so terribly angry, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,  and remember
        not iniquity forever.Behold, please look, we are all your people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  Your holy cities have become a wilderness;Zion has become a wilderness,Jerusalem
        a desolation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  Our holy and beautiful[[COMMENT(0)]] house,where our fathers praised
        you,has been burned by fire,and all our pleasant places have become ruins.  '
      comments:
      - number: '64:11 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  Will you restrain yourself at these things, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?Will
        you keep silent, and afflict us so terribly?'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment and Salvation'
      title: Judgment and Salvation
      number: 1
      content: "    I was ready to be sought by those who did not ask for me;I was
        ready to be found by those who did not seek me.I said, \u201CHere I am, here
        I am,\u201Dto a nation that was not called by[[COMMENT(0)]] my name.  "
      comments:
      - number: '65:1 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  I spread out my hands all the dayto a rebellious people,who walk
        in a way that is not good,following their own devices;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'a people who provoke meto my face continually,  sacrificing in gardensand
        making offerings on bricks;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "who sit in tombs,and spend the night in secret places;  who eat pig\u2019s
        flesh,and broth of tainted meat is in their vessels;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "who say, \u201CKeep to yourself,do not come near me, for I am too
        holy for you.\u201D  These are a smoke in my nostrils,a fire that burns all
        the day.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Behold, it is written before me:  \u201CI will not keep silent, but
        I will repay;  I will indeed repay into their lap  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "both your iniquities and your fathers\u2019 iniquities together,says
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;  because they made offerings on the mountains 
        and insulted me on the hills,I will measure into their lappayment for their
        former deeds.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '65:7 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  \u201CAs the new wine
        is found in the cluster,and they say, \u2018Do not destroy it,for there is
        a blessing in it,\u2019so I will do for my servants\u2019 sake,  and not
        destroy them all.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  I will bring forth offspring from Jacob,and from Judah possessors
        of my mountains;my chosen shall possess it,and my servants shall dwell there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  Sharon shall become a pasture for flocks,and the Valley of Achor
        a place for herds to lie down,for my people who have sought me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But you who forsake the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,who forget my
        holy mountain,who set a table for Fortuneand fill cups of mixed wine for
        Destiny,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "I will destine you to the sword,and all of you shall bow down to
        the slaughter,  because, when I called, you did not answer;when I spoke,
        you did not listen,  but you did what was evil in my eyesand chose what I
        did not delight in.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>:\u201CBehold,
        my servants shall eat,but you shall be hungry;behold, my servants shall drink,but
        you shall be thirsty;behold, my servants shall rejoice,but you shall be put
        to shame;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'behold, my servants shall sing for gladness of heart,but you shall
        cry out for pain of heartand shall wail for breaking of spirit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You shall leave your name to my chosen for a curse,and the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>
        will put you to death,but his servants he will call by another name,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: New Heavens and a New Earth'
      title: New Heavens and a New Earth
      number: 16
      content: 'so that he who blesses himself in the landshall bless himself by
        the God of truth,and he who takes an oath in the landshall swear by the God
        of truth;  because the former troubles are forgottenand are hidden from my
        eyes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CFor behold, I create new heavensand a new earth,and the former
        things shall not be rememberedor come into mind.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But be glad and rejoice foreverin that which I create;for behold,
        I create Jerusalem to be a joy,and her people to be a gladness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  I will rejoice in Jerusalemand be glad in my people;  no more shall
        be heard in it the sound of weepingand the cry of distress.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'No more shall there be in itan infant who lives but a few days,or
        an old man who does not fill out his days,for the young man shall die a hundred
        years old,and the sinner a hundred years old shall be accursed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  They shall build houses and inhabit them;they shall plant vineyards
        and eat their fruit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  They shall not build and another inhabit;they shall not plant and
        another eat;  for like the days of a tree shall the days of my people be,and
        my chosen shall long enjoy[[COMMENT(0)]] the work of their hands.  '
      comments:
      - number: '65:22 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  They shall not labor in vain  or bear children for calamity,[[COMMENT(0)]]for
        they shall be the offspring of the blessed of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and
        their descendants with them.  '
      comments:
      - number: '65:23 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '  Before they call I will answer;  while they are yet speaking I
        will hear.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "  The wolf and the lamb shall graze together;the lion shall eat straw
        like the ox,and dust shall be the serpent\u2019s food.  They shall not hurt
        or destroyin all my holy mountain,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Humble and Contrite in Spirit'
      title: The Humble and Contrite in Spirit
      number: 1
      content: "    Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  \u201CHeaven is my
        throne,and the earth is my footstool;what is the house that you would build
        for me,and what is the place of my rest?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  All these things my hand has made,and so all these things came
        to be,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  But this is the one to whom
        I will look:he who is humble and contrite in spiritand trembles at my word.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "  \u201CHe who slaughters an ox is like one who kills a man;he who
        sacrifices a lamb, like one who breaks a dog\u2019s neck;he who presents
        a grain offering, like one who offers pig\u2019s blood;he who makes a memorial
        offering of frankincense, like one who blesses an idol.  These have chosen
        their own ways,and their soul delights in their abominations;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "  I also will choose harsh treatment for themand bring their fears
        upon them,  because when I called, no one answered,when I spoke, they did
        not listen;  but they did what was evil in my eyesand chose that in which
        I did not delight.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Hear the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,you who tremble
        at his word:\u201CYour brothers who hate youand cast you out for my name\u2019s
        sakehave said, \u2018Let the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> be glorified,that
        we may see your joy\u2019;but it is they who shall be put to shame.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Rejoice with Jerusalem'
      title: Rejoice with Jerusalem
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CThe sound of an uproar from the city!A sound from the temple!The
        sound of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,  rendering recompense to his enemies!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  \u201CBefore she was in laborshe gave birth;before her pain came
        upon hershe delivered a son.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Who has heard such a thing?Who has seen such things?Shall a land
        be born in one day?Shall a nation be brought forth in one moment?For as soon
        as Zion was in laborshe brought forth her children.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Shall I bring to the point of birth and not cause to bring forth?\u201Dsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;\u201Cshall I, who cause to bring forth,
        shut the womb?\u201Dsays your God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "  \u201CRejoice with Jerusalem, and be glad for her,all you who love
        her;rejoice with her in joy,all you who mourn over her;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "that you may nurse and be satisfiedfrom her consoling breast;that
        you may drink deeply with delightfrom her glorious abundance.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '66:11 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "For thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  \u201CBehold, I will
        extend peace to her like a river,and the glory of the nations like an overflowing
        stream;and you shall nurse, you shall be carried upon her hip,and bounced
        upon her knees.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'As one whom his mother comforts,so I will comfort you;you shall be
        comforted in Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Final Judgment and Glory of the '
      title: 'Final Judgment and Glory of the '
      number: 14
      content: 'You shall see, and your heart shall rejoice;  your bones shall flourish
        like the grass;and the hand of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> shall be known
        to his servants,and he shall show his indignation against his enemies.<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CFor behold, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will come in fire,and
        his chariots like the whirlwind,to render his anger in fury,and his rebuke
        with flames of fire.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For by fire will the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> enter into judgment,and
        by his sword, with all flesh;and those slain by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        shall be many.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "  \u201CThose who sanctify and purify themselves to go into the gardens,
        following one in the midst, eating pig\u2019s flesh and the abomination and
        mice, shall come to an end together, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CFor I know[[COMMENT(0)]] their works and their thoughts, and
        the time is coming  to gather all nations and tongues. And they shall come
        and shall see my glory, "
      comments:
      - number: '66:18 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Syriac; Hebrew lacks Hebrew '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'and I will set a sign among them. And from them I will send survivors
        to the nations, to Tarshish, Pul, and Lud, who draw the bow, to Tubal and
        Javan, to the coastlands far away, that have not heard my fame or seen my
        glory. And they shall declare my glory among the nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And they shall bring all your brothers from all the nations as an
        offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, on horses and in chariots and
        in litters and on mules and on dromedaries, to my holy mountain Jerusalem,
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, just as the Israelites bring their
        grain offering in a clean vessel to the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And some of them also I will take for priests and for Levites, says
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CFor as the new heavens and the new earththat I makeshall remain
        before me, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,so shall your offspring and
        your name remain.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  From new moon to new moon,and from Sabbath to Sabbath,all flesh
        shall come to worship before me,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CAnd they shall go out and look on the dead bodies of the men
        who have rebelled against me. For their worm shall not die, their fire shall
        not be quenched, and they shall be an abhorrence to all flesh.\u201D"
      comments: []
